50 #define PARSE_UNSAFE(VAR_LINE, MIN_ARGS, _BLOCK_) \
51  this->AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, \
52  "Syntax check failed, parsing by legacy unsafe method..."); \
53  const int min_args = MIN_ARGS; \
54  Ogre::StringVector values; \
55  if (this->_ParseArgs(VAR_LINE, values, min_args) < min_args) \
56  { \
57  std::stringstream msg; \
58  msg << "Too few arguments, required number is " << min_args; \
59  this->AddMessage(VAR_LINE, Message::TYPE_WARNING, msg.str()); \
60  } \
61  else \
62  { \
63  _BLOCK_ \
64  }

66 Parser::Parser():
67  m_ror_minimass(0)
68 {
69  /* Push defaults */
70  m_ror_default_inertia = boost::shared_ptr<DefaultInertia>(new DefaultInertia);
71  m_ror_beam_defaults = boost::shared_ptr<BeamDefaults>(new BeamDefaults);
72  m_ror_node_defaults = boost::shared_ptr<NodeDefaults>(new NodeDefaults);
73 }

75 Parser::~Parser()
76 {}

78 void Parser::ParseLine(Ogre::String const & line)
79 {
80  unsigned int line_length = line.length();
81  if (line_length == 0)
82  {
83  m_current_line_number++;
84  return;
85  }
86 
87  bool line_finished = false;
88  bool scan_for_keyword = true;
89 
90  /* Check line type */
91  boost::smatch line_type_result;
92  if (m_in_block_comment)
93  {
94  if (boost::regex_match(line, Regexes::CHECK_BLOCK_COMMENT_END))
95  {
96  m_in_block_comment = false;
97  }
98  line_finished = true;
99  }
100  else if (m_in_description_section)
101  {
102  if (boost::regex_match(line, Regexes::CHECK_END_DESCRIPTION))
103  {
104  m_in_description_section = false;
105  }
106  else
107  {
108  m_definition->description.push_back(line);
109  }
110  line_finished = true;
111  }
112  else
113  {
114  if (boost::regex_search(line, line_type_result, Regexes::IDENTIFY_LINE_TYPE))
115  {
116  if (line_type_result[1].matched) /* Block comment start */
117  {
118  m_in_block_comment = true;
119  line_finished = true;
120  }
121  else if (line_type_result[2].matched || line_type_result[3].matched || line_type_result[4].matched) /* Comment line || blank line */
122  {
123  m_num_contiguous_blank_lines++;
124  line_finished = true;
125  }
126  else /* Line has content */
127  {
128  m_num_contiguous_blank_lines = 0;
129  }
130  }
131  }
132 
133  /* Continue? */
134  if (line_finished)
135  {
136  m_current_line_number++;
137  return;
138  }
139 
140  /* Prepare for switching file section */
141  Ogre::String const & current_module_name = m_current_module->name;
142  bool current_module_is_root = m_current_module == m_root_module;
143  bool module_changed = false;
144  Ogre::String new_module_name;
145  bool new_module_is_root = false;
146 
147  File::Section new_section = File::SECTION_INVALID;
148  File::Subsection new_subsection = File::SUBSECTION_INVALID;
149 
150  /* Detect keywords on current line */
151  /* NOTE: Please maintain alphabetical order */
152  if (scan_for_keyword)
153  {
154  File::Keyword keyword = IdentifyKeyword(line);
155  switch (keyword)
156  {
157  case (File::KEYWORD_INVALID): /* No new section */
158  break;
159 
160  case (File::KEYWORD_ADD_ANIMATION):
161  ParseDirectiveAddAnimation(line);
162  line_finished = true;
163  break;
164 
165  case (File::KEYWORD_AIRBRAKES):
166  new_section = File::SECTION_AIRBRAKES;
167  line_finished = true;
168  break;
169 
170  case (File::KEYWORD_ANIMATORS):
171  new_section = File::SECTION_ANIMATORS;
172  line_finished = true;
173  break;
174 
175  case (File::KEYWORD_ANTI_LOCK_BRAKES):
176  ParseAntiLockBrakes(line);
177  line_finished = true;
178  break;
179 
180  case (File::KEYWORD_AXLES):
181  new_section = File::SECTION_AXLES;
182  line_finished = true;
183  break;
184 
185  case (File::KEYWORD_AUTHOR):
186  ParseAuthor(line);
187  line_finished = true;
188  break;
189 
190  case (File::KEYWORD_BACKMESH):
191  if (m_current_section == File::SECTION_SUBMESH)
192  {
193  m_current_submesh->backmesh = true;
194  }
195  else
196  {
197  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Misplaced sub-directive 'backmesh' (belongs in section 'submesh'), ignoring...");
198  }
199  line_finished = true;
200  break;
201 
202  case (File::KEYWORD_BEAMS):
203  new_section = File::SECTION_BEAMS;
204  line_finished = true;
205  break;
206 
207  case (File::KEYWORD_BRAKES):
208  new_section = File::SECTION_BRAKES;
209  line_finished = true;
210  break;
211 
212  case (File::KEYWORD_CAB):
213  if (m_current_section == File::SECTION_SUBMESH)
214  {
215  new_subsection = File::SUBSECTION__SUBMESH__CAB;
216  }
217  else
218  {
219  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Misplaced sub-section 'cab' (belongs in section 'submesh'), ignoring...");
220  }
221  line_finished = true;
222  break;
223 
224  case (File::KEYWORD_CAMERAS):
225  new_section = File::SECTION_CAMERAS;
226  line_finished = true;
227  break;
228 
229  case (File::KEYWORD_CAMERARAIL):
230  new_section = File::SECTION_CAMERA_RAIL;
231  line_finished = true;
232  break;
233 
234  case (File::KEYWORD_CINECAM):
235  new_section = File::SECTION_CINECAM;
236  line_finished = true;
237  break;
238 
239  case (File::KEYWORD_COLLISIONBOXES):
240  new_section = File::SECTION_COLLISION_BOXES;
241  line_finished = true;
242  break;
243 
244  case (File::KEYWORD_COMMANDS):
245  new_section = File::SECTION_COMMANDS;
246  line_finished = true;
247  break;
248 
249  case (File::KEYWORD_COMMANDS2):
250  new_section = File::SECTION_COMMANDS_2;
251  line_finished = true;
252  break;
253 
254  case (File::KEYWORD_CONTACTERS):
255  new_section = File::SECTION_CONTACTERS;
256  line_finished = true;
257  break;
258 
259  case (File::KEYWORD_CRUISECONTROL):
260  ParseCruiseControl(line);
261  line_finished = true;
262  break;
263 
264  case (File::KEYWORD_DESCRIPTION):
265  m_in_description_section = true;
266  line_finished = true;
267  break;
268 
269  case (File::KEYWORD_DETACHER_GROUP):
270  ParseDirectiveDetacherGroup(line);
271  line_finished = true;
272  break;
273 
274  case (File::KEYWORD_DISABLEDEFAULTSOUNDS):
275  if (! current_module_is_root)
276  {
277  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, "Directive 'disabledefaultsounds' has global effect and should not appear in a module");
278  }
279  m_definition->disable_default_sounds = true;
280  line_finished = true;
281  break;
282 
283  case (File::KEYWORD_ENABLE_ADVANCED_DEFORMATION):
284  if (! current_module_is_root)
285  {
286  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, "Directive 'enable_advanced_deformation' has global effect and should not appear in a module");
287  }
288  m_definition->enable_advanced_deformation = true;
289  line_finished = true;
290  break;
291 
292  case (File::KEYWORD_END):
293  /* Ignore silently */
294  line_finished = true;
295  break;
296 
297  case (File::KEYWORD_END_SECTION):
298  module_changed = true;
299  new_module_is_root = true;
300  line_finished = true;
301  break;
302 
303  case (File::KEYWORD_ENGINE):
304  new_section = File::SECTION_ENGINE;
305  line_finished = true;
306  break;
307 
308  case (File::KEYWORD_ENGOPTION):
309  new_section = File::SECTION_ENGOPTION;
310  line_finished = true;
311  break;
312 
313  case (File::KEYWORD_ENGTURBO) :
314  new_section = File::SECTION_ENGTURBO;
315  line_finished = true;
316  break;
317 
318  case (File::KEYWORD_ENVMAP):
319  /* Ignored */
320  line_finished = true;
321  break;
322 
323  case (File::KEYWORD_EXHAUSTS):
324  new_section = File::SECTION_EXHAUSTS;
325  line_finished = true;
326  break;
327 
328  case (File::KEYWORD_EXTCAMERA):
329  ParseExtCamera(line);
330  line_finished = true;
331  break;
332 
333  case (File::KEYWORD_FILEFORMATVERSION):
334  if (! current_module_is_root)
335  {
336  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, "Inline section 'fileformatversion' has global effect and should not appear in a module");
337  }
338  ParseFileFormatVersion(line);
339  line_finished = true;
340  break;
341 
342  case (File::KEYWORD_FILEINFO):
343  if (! current_module_is_root)
344  {
345  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, "Inline-section 'fileinfo' has global effect and should not appear in a module");
346  }
347  ParseFileinfo(line);
348  line_finished = true;
349  break;
350 
351  case (File::KEYWORD_FIXES):
352  new_section = File::SECTION_FIXES;
353  line_finished = true;
354  break;
355 
356  case (File::KEYWORD_FLARES):
357  new_section = File::SECTION_FLARES;
358  line_finished = true;
359  break;
360 
361  case (File::KEYWORD_FLARES2):
362  new_section = File::SECTION_FLARES_2;
363  line_finished = true;
364  break;
365 
366  case (File::KEYWORD_FLEXBODIES):
367  new_section = File::SECTION_FLEXBODIES;
368  line_finished = true;
369  break;
370 
371  case (File::KEYWORD_FLEXBODY_CAMERA_MODE):
372  ParseDirectiveFlexbodyCameraMode(line);
373  line_finished = true;
374  break;
375 
376  case (File::KEYWORD_FLEXBODYWHEELS):
377  new_section = File::SECTION_FLEX_BODY_WHEELS;
378  line_finished = true;
379  break;
380 
381  case (File::KEYWORD_FORWARDCOMMANDS):
382  if (! current_module_is_root)
383  {
384  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, "Directive 'forwardcommands' has global effect and should not appear in a module");
385  }
386  m_definition->forward_commands = true;
387  line_finished = true;
388  break;
389 
390  case (File::KEYWORD_FUSEDRAG):
391  new_section = File::SECTION_FUSEDRAG;
392  line_finished = true;
393  break;
394 
395  case (File::KEYWORD_GLOBALS):
396  new_section = File::SECTION_GLOBALS;
397  line_finished = true;
398  break;
399 
400  case (File::KEYWORD_GUID):
401  ParseGuid(line);
402  line_finished = true;
403  break;
404 
405  case (File::KEYWORD_GUISETTINGS):
406  new_section = File::SECTION_GUI_SETTINGS;
407  line_finished = true;
408  break;
409 
410  case (File::KEYWORD_HELP):
411  new_section = File::SECTION_HELP;
412  line_finished = true;
413  break;
414 
415  case (File::KEYWORD_HIDE_IN_CHOOSER):
416  if (! current_module_is_root)
417  {
418  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, "Directive 'hideInChooser' has global effect and should not appear in a module");
419  }
420  m_definition->hide_in_chooser = true;
421  line_finished = true;
422  break;
423 
424  case (File::KEYWORD_HOOKGROUP):
425  /* Not supported yet, ignore */
426  line_finished = true;
427  break;
428 
429  case (File::KEYWORD_HOOKS):
430  new_section = File::SECTION_HOOKS;
431  line_finished = true;
432  break;
433 
434  case (File::KEYWORD_HYDROS):
435  new_section = File::SECTION_HYDROS;
436  line_finished = true;
437  break;
438 
439  case (File::KEYWORD_IMPORTCOMMANDS):
440  m_definition->import_commands = true;
441  line_finished = true;
442  break;
443 
444  case (File::KEYWORD_LOCKGROUPS):
445  new_section = File::SECTION_LOCKGROUPS;
446  line_finished = true;
447  break;
448 
449  case (File::KEYWORD_LOCKGROUP_DEFAULT_NOLOCK):
450  if (! current_module_is_root)

745  case (File::KEYWORD_WINGS):
746  new_section = File::SECTION_WINGS;
747  line_finished = true;
748  break;
749 
750  }
751  }
752 
753  if (module_changed)
754  {
755  new_section = File::SECTION_NONE; /* Make parser commit unfinished work, actual module switch happens afterwards. */
756  }
757 
758  /* Section-specific switch logic */
759  if (new_section != File::SECTION_INVALID)
760  {
761  /* Exit sections */
762  if (m_current_section == File::SECTION_SUBMESH)
763  {
764  m_current_module->submeshes.push_back(*m_current_submesh);
765  m_current_submesh.reset();
766  m_current_subsection = File::SUBSECTION_NONE;
767  }
768  else if (m_current_section == File::SECTION_CAMERA_RAIL)
769  {
770  if (m_current_camera_rail->nodes.size() == 0)
771  {
772  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, "Empty section 'camerarail', ignoring...");
773  }
774  else
775  {
776  m_current_module->camera_rails.push_back(*m_current_camera_rail);
777  m_current_camera_rail.reset();
778  }
779  }
780  else if (m_current_section == File::SECTION_FLEXBODIES)
781  {
782  m_current_subsection = File::SUBSECTION_NONE;
783  }
784 
785  /* Enter sections */
786  if (new_section == File::SECTION_SUBMESH)
787  {
788  m_current_submesh = boost::shared_ptr<Submesh>( new Submesh() );
789  }
790  else if (new_section == File::SECTION_CAMERA_RAIL)
791  {
792  m_current_camera_rail = boost::shared_ptr<CameraRail>( new CameraRail() );
793  }
794  else if (new_section == File::SECTION_FLEXBODIES)
795  {
796  m_current_subsection = File::SUBSECTION__FLEXBODIES__PROPLIKE_LINE;
797  }
798  else if (new_section == File::SECTION_GUI_SETTINGS)
799  {
800  if (m_current_module->gui_settings == nullptr)
801  {
802  m_current_module->gui_settings = boost::shared_ptr<GuiSettings> ( new GuiSettings() );
803  }
804  }
805 
806  m_current_section = new_section;
807  }
808  else if (new_subsection != File::SUBSECTION_INVALID)
809  {
810  m_current_subsection = new_subsection;
811  }
812 
813  /* Module-switching */
814  if (module_changed)
815  {
816  m_last_flexbody.reset(); // Set to nullptr
817 
818  if (new_module_is_root)
819  {
820  if (current_module_is_root)
821  {
822  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Misplaced keyword 'end_section', ignoring...");
823  }
824  else
825  {
826  RestoreRootModule();
827  }
828  }
829  else
830  {
831  if (current_module_name == new_module_name)
832  {
833  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Attempt to re-enter current module, ignoring...");
834  }
835  else
836  {
837  SetCurrentModule(new_module_name);
838  }
839  }
840  }
841 
842  /* Continue? */
843  if (line_finished)
844  {
845  m_current_line_number++;
846  return;
847  }
848 
849  /* Parse current section, if any */
850  /* NOTE: Please maintain alphabetical order */
851  switch (m_current_section)
852  {
853 
854  case (File::SECTION_AIRBRAKES):
855  ParseAirbrakes(line);
856  line_finished = true;
857  break;
858 
859  case (File::SECTION_ANIMATORS):
860  ParseAnimator(line);
861  line_finished = true;
862  break;
863 
864  case (File::SECTION_AXLES):
865  ParseAxles(line);
866  line_finished = true;
867  break;
868 
869  case (File::SECTION_TRUCK_NAME):
870  m_definition->name = Ogre::String(line);
871  Ogre::StringUtil::trim(m_definition->name);
872  m_current_section = File::SECTION_NONE;
873  line_finished = true;
874  break;
875 
876  case (File::SECTION_BEAMS):
877  ParseBeams(line);
878  line_finished = true;
879  break;
880 
881  case (File::SECTION_BRAKES):
882  ParseBrakes(line);
883  line_finished = true;
884  break;
885 
886  case (File::SECTION_CAMERAS):
887  ParseCameras(line);
888  line_finished = true;
889  break;
890 
891  case (File::SECTION_CAMERA_RAIL):
892  ParseCameraRails(line);
893  line_finished = true;
894  break;
895 
896  case (File::SECTION_CINECAM):
897  ParseCinecam(line);
898  line_finished = true;
899  break;
900 
901  case (File::SECTION_COMMANDS):
902  ParseCommand(line);
903  line_finished = true;
904  break;
905 
906  case (File::SECTION_COMMANDS_2):
907  ParseCommand2(line);
908  line_finished = true;
909  break;
910 
911  case (File::SECTION_COLLISION_BOXES):
912  ParseCollisionBox(line);
913  line_finished = true;
914  break;
915 
916  case (File::SECTION_CONTACTERS):
917  ParseContacter(line);
918  line_finished = true;
919  break;
920 
921  case (File::SECTION_ENGINE):
922  ParseEngine(line);
923  line_finished = true;
924  break;
925 
926  case (File::SECTION_ENGOPTION):
927  ParseEngoption(line);
928  line_finished = true;
929  break;
930 
931  case (File::SECTION_ENGTURBO) :
932  ParseEngturbo(line);
933  line_finished = true;
934  break;
935

937  ParseExhaust(line);
938  line_finished = true;
939  break;
940

942  ParseFixes(line);
943  line_finished = true;
944  break;
945 
946  case (File::SECTION_FLARES):
947  ParseFlare(line);
948  line_finished = true;
949  break;
950

952  ParseFlare2(line);
953  line_finished = true;
954  break;
955

959  break;

963  line_finished = true;

968  line_finished = true;

973  line_finished = true;

977  ParseGuiSettings(line);

979  break;

1163  };
1164 
1165  /* Continue? */
1166  if (line_finished)
1167  {
1168  m_current_line_number++;
1169  return;
1170  }
1171 }

1192 void Parser::ParseWing(Ogre::String const & line)
1193 {
1194 
1195  boost::smatch results;
1196  try
1197  {
1198  if (! boost::regex_search(line, results, Regexes::SECTION_WINGS))
1199  {
1200  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid line, ignoring...");
1201  return;
1202  }
1203  }
1204  catch(std::runtime_error e)
1205  {
1206  std::stringstream msg;
1207  msg << "Wing not parsed, internal parser failure occured, message: " << e.what();
1208  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_FATAL_ERROR, msg.str());
1209  return;
1210  }
1211  /* NOTE: Positions in 'results' array match E_CAPTURE*() positions (starting with 1) in the respective regex. */
1212 
1213  Wing wing;
1214 
1215  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < 8; i++)
1216  {
1217  wing.nodes[i] = _ParseNodeRef(results[i + 1]);
1218  }
1219 
1220  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < 8; i++)
1221  {
1222  wing.tex_coords[i] = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[i + 9]);
1223  }
1224 
1225  if (results[17].matched)
1226  {
1227  std::string control_surface_str = results[18];
1228  wing.control_surface = Wing::Control(control_surface_str.at(0));
1229 
1230  if (results[19].matched)
1231  {
1232  wing.chord_point = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[20]);
1233 
1234  if (results[21].matched)
1235  {
1236  wing.min_deflection = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[22]);
1237 
1238  if (results[23].matched)
1239  {
1240  wing.max_deflection = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[24]);
1241 
1242  if (results[25].matched)
1243  {
1244  wing.airfoil = results[26];
1245 
1246  if (results[27].matched)
1247  {
1248  wing.efficacy_coef = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[28]);
1249  }
1250  }
1251  }
1252  }
1253  }
1254  }
1255 
1256  m_current_module->wings.push_back(wing);
1257 }

1259 void Parser::ParseSetCollisionRange(Ogre::String const & line)
1260 {
1261  boost::smatch results;
1262  if (! boost::regex_search(line, results, Regexes::INLINE_SECTION_SET_COLLISION_RANGE))
1263  {
1264  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid line, ignoring...");
1265  return;
1266  }
1267  /* NOTE: Positions in 'results' array match E_CAPTURE*() positions (starting with 1) in the respective regex. */
1268 
1269  if (results[1].matched)
1270  {
1271  m_definition->collision_range = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[1]);
1272  m_definition->_collision_range_set = true;
1273  }
1274 }

1276 void Parser::ParseWheel2(Ogre::String const & line)
1277 {
1278  boost::smatch results;
1279  if (! boost::regex_search(line, results, Regexes::SECTION_WHEELS2))
1280  {
1281  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid line, ignoring...");
1282  return;
1283  }
1284  /* NOTE: Positions in 'results' array match E_CAPTURE*() positions (starting with 1) in the respective regex. */
1285 
1286  Wheel2 wheel_2;
1287  wheel_2.node_defaults = m_user_node_defaults;
1288  wheel_2.beam_defaults = m_user_beam_defaults;
1289 
1290  wheel_2.rim_radius = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[1]);
1291  wheel_2.tyre_radius = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[2]);
1292  wheel_2.width = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[3]);
1293  wheel_2.num_rays = STR_PARSE_INT(results[4]);
1294  wheel_2.nodes[0] = _ParseNodeRef(results[5]);
1295  wheel_2.nodes[1] = _ParseNodeRef(results[6]);
1296  wheel_2.rigidity_node = _ParseNodeRef(results[7]);
1297  if (wheel_2.rigidity_node.Num() == 9999) /* Special null value */
1298  {
1299  wheel_2.rigidity_node.Invalidate();
1300  }
1301 
1302  if (m_sequential_importer.IsEnabled())
1303  {
1304  m_sequential_importer.GenerateNodesForWheel(File::KEYWORD_WHEELS2, wheel_2.num_rays, wheel_2.rigidity_node.IsValidAnyState());
1305  }
1306 
1307  unsigned int braking = STR_PARSE_INT(results[8]);
1308  if (braking >= 0 && braking <= 4)
1309  {
1310  wheel_2.braking = Wheels::Braking(braking);
1311  }
1312  else
1313  {
1314  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, "Invalid 'braking' value, setting BRAKING_NO (0).");
1315  }
1316 
1317  unsigned int propulsion = STR_PARSE_INT(results[9]);
1318  if (propulsion >= 0 && propulsion <= 2)
1319  {
1320  wheel_2.propulsion = Wheels::Propulsion(propulsion);
1321  }
1322  else
1323  {
1324  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, "Invalid 'propulsion' value, setting PROPULSION_NONE (0).");
1325  }
1326  wheel_2.reference_arm_node = _ParseNodeRef(results[10]);
1327 
1328  wheel_2.mass = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[11]);
1329  wheel_2.rim_springiness = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[12]);
1330  wheel_2.rim_damping = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[13]);
1331  wheel_2.tyre_springiness = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[14]);
1332  wheel_2.tyre_damping = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[15]);
1333  wheel_2.face_material_name = results[16];
1334  wheel_2.band_material_name = results[17];
1335 
1336  m_current_module->wheels_2.push_back(wheel_2);
1337 }

1339 void Parser::ParseWheel(Ogre::String const & line)
1340 {
1341  boost::smatch results;
1342  if (! boost::regex_search(line, results, Regexes::SECTION_WHEELS))
1343  {
1344  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid line, ignoring...");
1345  return;
1346  }
1347  /* NOTE: Positions in 'results' array match E_CAPTURE*() positions (starting with 1) in the respective regex. */
1348 
1349  Wheel wheel;
1350  wheel.node_defaults = m_user_node_defaults;
1351  wheel.beam_defaults = m_user_beam_defaults;
1352 
1353  wheel.radius = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[1]);
1354  wheel.width = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[2]);
1355  wheel.num_rays = STR_PARSE_INT(results[3]);
1356  wheel.nodes[0] = _ParseNodeRef(results[4]);
1357  wheel.nodes[1] = _ParseNodeRef(results[5]);
1358  wheel.rigidity_node = _ParseNodeRef(results[6]);
1359  if (wheel.rigidity_node.Num() == 9999) /* Special null value */
1360  {
1361  wheel.rigidity_node.Invalidate();
1362  }
1363 
1364  if (m_sequential_importer.IsEnabled())
1365  {
1366  m_sequential_importer.GenerateNodesForWheel(File::KEYWORD_WHEELS, wheel.num_rays, wheel.rigidity_node.IsValidAnyState());
1367  }
1368 
1369  unsigned int braking = STR_PARSE_INT(results[7]);
1370  if (braking >= 0 && braking <= 4)
1371  {
1372  wheel.braking = Wheels::Braking(braking);
1373  }
1374  else
1375  {
1376  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, "Invalid 'braking' value, setting BRAKING_NO (0).");
1377  }
1378 
1379  unsigned int propulsion = STR_PARSE_INT(results[8]);
1380  if (propulsion >= 0 && propulsion <= 2)
1381  {
1382  wheel.propulsion = Wheels::Propulsion(propulsion);
1383  }
1384  else
1385  {
1386  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, "Invalid 'propulsion' value, setting PROPULSION_NONE (0).");
1387  }
1388  wheel.reference_arm_node = _ParseNodeRef(results[9]);
1389 
1390  wheel.mass = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[10]);
1391  wheel.springiness = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[11]);
1392  wheel.damping = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[12]);
1393  wheel.face_material_name = results[13];
1394  wheel.band_material_name = results[14];
1395 
1396  m_current_module->wheels.push_back(wheel);
1397 }
1398 
1399 void Parser::ParseTractionControl(Ogre::String const & line)
1400 {
1401  if (m_current_module->traction_control != nullptr)
1402  {
1403  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, "Multiple inline-sections 'TractionControl' in a module, using last one ...");
1404  }
1405  m_current_module->traction_control = boost::shared_ptr<TractionControl>( new TractionControl() );
1406 
1407  boost::smatch results;
1408  if (! boost::regex_search(line, results, Regexes::SECTION_TRACTION_CONTROL))
1409  {
1410  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid line, ignoring...");
1411  return;
1412  }
1413  /* NOTE: Positions in 'results' array match E_CAPTURE*() positions (starting with 1) in the respective regex. */
1414 
1415  m_current_module->traction_control->regulation_force = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[1]);
1416  m_current_module->traction_control->wheel_slip = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[2]);
1417 
1418  if (results[3].matched)
1419  {
1420  m_current_module->traction_control->fade_speed = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[4]);
1421 
1422  if (results[5].matched)
1423  {
1424  m_current_module->traction_control->pulse_per_sec = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[6]);
1425 
1426  if (results[7].matched)
1427  {
1428  /* parse mode */
1429  Ogre::StringVector tokens = Ogre::StringUtil::split(results[8], "&");
1430  Ogre::StringVector::iterator iter = tokens.begin();
1431  for ( ; iter != tokens.end(); iter++)
1432  {
1433  boost::smatch results;
1434  if (! boost::regex_search(*iter, results, Regexes::TRACTION_CONTROL_MODE))
1435  {
1436  AddMessage(*iter, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid mode keyword, ignoring whole line...");
1437  return;
1438  }
1439  /* NOTE: Positions in 'results' array match E_CAPTURE*() positions (starting with 1) in the respective regex. */
1440 
1441  if (results[1].matched)
1442  {
1443  BITMASK_SET_1(m_current_module->traction_control->mode, AntiLockBrakes::MODE_ON);
1444  BITMASK_SET_0(m_current_module->traction_control->mode, AntiLockBrakes::MODE_OFF);
1445  }
1446  else if (results[2].matched)
1447  {
1448  BITMASK_SET_1(m_current_module->traction_control->mode, AntiLockBrakes::MODE_OFF);
1449  BITMASK_SET_0(m_current_module->traction_control->mode, AntiLockBrakes::MODE_ON);
1450  }
1451  else if (results[3].matched)
1452  {
1453  BITMASK_SET_1(m_current_module->traction_control->mode, AntiLockBrakes::MODE_NO_DASHBOARD);
1454  }
1455  else if (results[4].matched)
1456  {
1457  BITMASK_SET_1(m_current_module->traction_control->mode, AntiLockBrakes::MODE_NO_TOGGLE);
1458  }
1459  }
1460  }
1461  }
1462  }
1463 }

1569 void Parser::VerifyAndProcessDirectiveSetNodeDefaults(
1570  Ogre::String const & line,
1571  float load_weight,
1572  float friction,
1573  float volume,
1574  float surface,
1575  unsigned int options)

1578

1580  m_user_node_defaults->friction = (friction < 0) ? m_ror_node_defaults->friction : friction;
1581  m_user_node_defaults->volume = (volume < 0) ? m_ror_node_defaults->volume : volume;
1582  m_user_node_defaults->surface = (surface < 0) ? m_ror_node_defaults->surface : surface;
1583 
1584  m_user_node_defaults->options = options;

1587 void Parser::LogParsedDirectiveSetNodeDefaultsData(Ogre::String const & line, float load_weight, float friction, float volume, float surface, unsigned int options)
1588 {
1589  std::stringstream msg;
1590  msg << "Parsed data for verification:"
1591  << "\n\tLoadWeight: " << load_weight
1592  << "\n\t Friction: " << friction
1593  << "\n\t Volume: " << volume
1594  << "\n\t Surface: " << surface
1595  << "\n\t Options: ";
1596 
1597  if (BITMASK_IS_1(options, Node::OPTION_l_LOAD_WEIGHT) ) { msg << " l_LOAD_WEIGHT"; }
1598  if (BITMASK_IS_1(options, Node::OPTION_n_MOUSE_GRAB) ) { msg << " n_MOUSE_GRAB"; }
1599  if (BITMASK_IS_1(options, Node::OPTION_m_NO_MOUSE_GRAB) ) { msg << " m_NO_MOUSE_GRAB"; }
1600  if (BITMASK_IS_1(options, Node::OPTION_f_NO_SPARKS) ) { msg << " f_NO_SPARKS"; }
1601  if (BITMASK_IS_1(options, Node::OPTION_x_EXHAUST_POINT) ) { msg << " x_EXHAUST_POINT"; }
1602  if (BITMASK_IS_1(options, Node::OPTION_y_EXHAUST_DIRECTION) ) { msg << " y_EXHAUST_DIRECTION"; }
1603  if (BITMASK_IS_1(options, Node::OPTION_c_NO_GROUND_CONTACT) ) { msg << " c_NO_GROUND_CONTACT"; }
1604  if (BITMASK_IS_1(options, Node::OPTION_h_HOOK_POINT) ) { msg << " h_HOOK_POINT"; }
1605  if (BITMASK_IS_1(options, Node::OPTION_e_TERRAIN_EDIT_POINT)) { msg << " e_TERRAIN_EDIT_POINT"; }
1606  if (BITMASK_IS_1(options, Node::OPTION_b_EXTRA_BUOYANCY) ) { msg << " b_EXTRA_BUOYANCY"; }
1607  if (BITMASK_IS_1(options, Node::OPTION_p_NO_PARTICLES) ) { msg << " p_NO_PARTICLES"; }
1608  if (BITMASK_IS_1(options, Node::OPTION_L_LOG) ) { msg << " L_LOG"; }
1609 
1610  this->AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, msg.str());
1611 }

1613 void Parser::ParseDirectiveSetNodeDefaultsUnsafe(Ogre::String const & line)
1614 {
1615  PARSE_UNSAFE(line, 2,
1616  {
1617  int num_args = values.size();
1618 
1619  // NOTE: Arguments start at index [1], [0] is the keyword
1620  float load_weight = STR_PARSE_REAL(values[1]);
1621  float friction = (num_args > 2) ? STR_PARSE_REAL(values[2]) : -1;
1622  float volume = (num_args > 3) ? STR_PARSE_REAL(values[3]) : -1;
1623  float surface = (num_args > 4) ? STR_PARSE_REAL(values[4]) : -1;
1624  unsigned int options = 0;
1625  if (num_args > 5) { this->_ParseNodeOptions(options, values[5]); }
1626 
1627  this->LogParsedDirectiveSetNodeDefaultsData(line, load_weight, friction, volume, surface, options);
1628  this->VerifyAndProcessDirectiveSetNodeDefaults(line, load_weight, friction, volume, surface, options);
1629  });
1630 }
1631 
1632 void Parser::ParseDirectiveSetNodeDefaults(Ogre::String const & line)
1633 {
1634  boost::smatch results;
1635  if (! boost::regex_search(line, results, Regexes::DIRECTIVE_SET_NODE_DEFAULTS))
1636  {
1637  this->ParseDirectiveSetNodeDefaultsUnsafe(line);
1638  return;
1639  }
1640  /* NOTE: Positions in 'results' array match E_CAPTURE*() positions (starting with 1) in the respective regex. */
1641 
1642  // NOTE: -1 resets to default value
1643  float load_weight = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[1]);
1644  float friction = (results[2].matched) ? STR_PARSE_REAL(results[4]) : -1;
1645  float volume = (results[4].matched) ? STR_PARSE_REAL(results[7]) : -1;
1646  float surface = (results[6].matched) ? STR_PARSE_REAL(results[10]) : -1;
1647 
1648  unsigned int options = 0;
1649  if (results[11].matched)
1650  {
1651  this->_ParseNodeOptions(options, results[13]);
1652  }
1653 
1654  this->VerifyAndProcessDirectiveSetNodeDefaults(line, load_weight, friction, volume, surface, options);
1655 }
1656 
1657 void Parser::_ParseNodeOptions(unsigned int & options, const std::string & options_str)
1658 {
1659  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < options_str.length(); i++)
1660  {
1661  const char c = options_str.at(i);
1662  switch(c)
1663  {
1664  case 'l':
1665  BITMASK_SET_1(options, Node::OPTION_l_LOAD_WEIGHT);
1666  break;
1667  case 'n':
1668  BITMASK_SET_1(options, Node::OPTION_n_MOUSE_GRAB);
1669  BITMASK_SET_0(options, Node::OPTION_m_NO_MOUSE_GRAB);
1670  break;
1671  case 'm':
1672  BITMASK_SET_1(options, Node::OPTION_m_NO_MOUSE_GRAB);
1673  BITMASK_SET_0(options, Node::OPTION_n_MOUSE_GRAB);
1674  break;
1675  case 'f':
1676  BITMASK_SET_1(options, Node::OPTION_f_NO_SPARKS);
1677  break;
1678  case 'x':
1679  BITMASK_SET_1(options, Node::OPTION_x_EXHAUST_POINT);
1680  break;
1681  case 'y':
1682  BITMASK_SET_1(options, Node::OPTION_y_EXHAUST_DIRECTION);
1683  break;
1684  case 'c':
1685  BITMASK_SET_1(options, Node::OPTION_c_NO_GROUND_CONTACT);
1686  break;
1687  case 'h':
1688  BITMASK_SET_1(options, Node::OPTION_h_HOOK_POINT);
1689  break;
1690  case 'e':
1691  BITMASK_SET_1(options, Node::OPTION_e_TERRAIN_EDIT_POINT);
1692  break;
1693  case 'b':
1694  BITMASK_SET_1(options, Node::OPTION_b_EXTRA_BUOYANCY);
1695  break;
1696  case 'p':
1697  BITMASK_SET_1(options, Node::OPTION_p_NO_PARTICLES);
1698  break;
1699  case 'L':
1700  BITMASK_SET_1(options, Node::OPTION_L_LOG);
1701  break;
1702 
1703  default:
1704  this->AddMessage(options_str, Message::TYPE_WARNING, std::string("Ignoring invalid option: ") + c);
1705  break;
1706  }
1707  }
1708 }
1709 
1710 void Parser::ParseDirectiveSetManagedMaterialsOptions(Ogre::String const & line)
1711 {
1712  boost::smatch results;
1713  if (! boost::regex_search(line, results, Regexes::DIRECTIVE_SET_MANAGEDMATERIALS_OPTIONS))
1714  {
1715  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid line, ignoring...");
1716  return;
1717  }
1718  /* NOTE: Positions in 'results' array match E_CAPTURE*() positions (starting with 1) in the respective regex. */
1719 
1720  /* Param 1: double-sided */
1721  Ogre::String input = results[1];
1722  int double_sided = STR_PARSE_INT(input); /* Let's do it the way old parser did, even though "input" can be any string */
1723  if (! boost::regex_match(input, boost::regex("0|1", boost::regex::extended)))
1724  {
1725  AddMessage(
1726  line,
1727  Message::TYPE_WARNING,
1728  "Directive 'set_managedmaterials_options':"
1729  " Invalid value of parameter ~1: '" + input + "', should be only '0' or '1'."
1730  " Interpreting as '0' for backwards compatibility. Please fix."
1731  );
1732  }
1733  m_current_managed_material_options.double_sided = double_sided != 0;
1734 }

1766 void Parser::ParseDirectiveSetBeamDefaults(Ogre::String const & line)
1767 {
1768  boost::smatch results;
1769  if (! boost::regex_search(line, results, Regexes::DIRECTIVE_SET_BEAM_DEFAULTS))
1770  {
1771  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid line, ignoring...");
1772  return;
1773  }
1774  /* NOTE: Positions in 'results' array match E_CAPTURE*() positions (starting with 1) in the respective regex. */
1775 
1776  m_user_beam_defaults = boost::shared_ptr<BeamDefaults>( new BeamDefaults(*m_user_beam_defaults) );
1777  /*
1778  What's the state of "enable_advanced_deformation" feature at this point?
1779  Directive "enable_advanced_deformation" alters the effects of BeamDefaults
1780  Since the old parser worked on-the-fly, only BeamDefaults defined after the directive were affected
1781  */
1782  m_user_beam_defaults->_enable_advanced_deformation = m_definition->enable_advanced_deformation;
1783  /*
1784  The "_enable_advanced_deformation" must only be aplied to BeamDefaults supplied by users,
1785  not on the initial defaults used by parser.
1786  */
1787  m_user_beam_defaults->_is_user_defined = true;
1788 
1789  /* Springiness */
1790  float default_spring = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[1]);
1791  if (default_spring < 0) /* NULL value => reset to default */
1792  {
1793  m_user_beam_defaults->springiness = m_ror_beam_defaults->springiness;
1794  BITMASK_SET_0(m_user_beam_defaults->_user_specified_fields, BeamDefaults::PARAM_SPRINGINESS);
1795  }
1796  else
1797  {
1798  m_user_beam_defaults->springiness = default_spring;
1799  BITMASK_SET_1(m_user_beam_defaults->_user_specified_fields, BeamDefaults::PARAM_SPRINGINESS);
1800  }
1801 
1802  /* Damping constant */
1803  if (results[2].matched)
1804  {
1805  float default_damp = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[3]);
1806  if (default_damp < 0) /* NULL value => reset to default */
1807  {
1808  m_user_beam_defaults->damping_constant = m_ror_beam_defaults->damping_constant;
1809  BITMASK_SET_0(m_user_beam_defaults->_user_specified_fields, BeamDefaults::PARAM_DAMPING_CONSTANT);
1810  }
1811  else
1812  {
1813  m_user_beam_defaults->damping_constant = default_damp;
1814  BITMASK_SET_1(m_user_beam_defaults->_user_specified_fields, BeamDefaults::PARAM_DAMPING_CONSTANT);
1815  }
1816  }
1817  else
1818  {
1819  return;
1820  }
1821 
1822  /* Deformation threshold constant */
1823  if (results[4].matched)
1824  {
1825  float default_deform = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[5]);
1826  if (default_deform < 0) /* NULL value => reset to default */
1827  {
1828  m_user_beam_defaults->deformation_threshold_constant = m_ror_beam_defaults->deformation_threshold_constant;
1829  BITMASK_SET_0(m_user_beam_defaults->_user_specified_fields, BeamDefaults::PARAM_DEFORM_THRESHOLD_CONSTANT);
1830  }
1831  else
1832  {
1833  m_user_beam_defaults->deformation_threshold_constant = default_deform;
1834  BITMASK_SET_1(m_user_beam_defaults->_user_specified_fields, BeamDefaults::PARAM_DEFORM_THRESHOLD_CONSTANT);
1835  }
1836  }
1837  else
1838  {
1839  return;
1840  }
1841 
1842  /* Breaking threshold constant */
1843  if (results[6].matched)
1844  {
1845  float default_break = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[7]);
1846  if (default_break < 0) /* NULL value => reset to default */
1847  {
1848  m_user_beam_defaults->breaking_threshold_constant = m_ror_beam_defaults->breaking_threshold_constant;
1849  BITMASK_SET_0(m_user_beam_defaults->_user_specified_fields, BeamDefaults::PARAM_DEFORM_THRESHOLD_CONSTANT);
1850  }
1851  else
1852  {
1853  m_user_beam_defaults->breaking_threshold_constant = default_break;
1854  BITMASK_SET_1(m_user_beam_defaults->_user_specified_fields, BeamDefaults::PARAM_BREAK_THRESHOLD_CONSTANT);
1855  }
1856  }
1857  else
1858  {
1859  return;
1860  }
1861 
1862  /* Beam diameter */
1863  if (results[8].matched)
1864  {
1865  float default_beam_diameter = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[9]);
1866  if (default_beam_diameter < 0) /* NULL value => reset to default */
1867  {
1868  m_user_beam_defaults->visual_beam_diameter = m_ror_beam_defaults->visual_beam_diameter;
1869  BITMASK_SET_0(m_user_beam_defaults->_user_specified_fields, BeamDefaults::PARAM_BEAM_DIAMETER);
1870  }
1871  else
1872  {
1873  m_user_beam_defaults->visual_beam_diameter = default_beam_diameter;
1874  BITMASK_SET_1(m_user_beam_defaults->_user_specified_fields, BeamDefaults::PARAM_BEAM_DIAMETER);
1875  }
1876  }
1877  else
1878  {
1879  return;
1880  }
1881 
1882  if (results[10].matched)
1883  {
1884  m_user_beam_defaults->beam_material_name = results[11];
1885  }
1886  else
1887  {
1888  return;
1889  }
1890 
1891  /* Plastic deformation coefficient */
1892  if (results[12].matched)
1893  {
1894  float default_plastic_coefficient = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[13]);
1895  if (default_plastic_coefficient < 0) /* NULL value => reset to default */
1896  {
1897  m_user_beam_defaults->plastic_deformation_coefficient = m_ror_beam_defaults->plastic_deformation_coefficient;
1898  BITMASK_SET_0(m_user_beam_defaults->_user_specified_fields, BeamDefaults::PARAM_PLASTIC_DEFORM_COEFFICIENT);
1899  }
1900  else
1901  {
1902  m_user_beam_defaults->plastic_deformation_coefficient = default_plastic_coefficient;
1903  BITMASK_SET_1(m_user_beam_defaults->_user_specified_fields, BeamDefaults::PARAM_PLASTIC_DEFORM_COEFFICIENT);
1904  }
1905  }
1906 
1907  return;
1908 }

1930 
1931 void Parser::VerifyAndProcessMeshWheel(Ogre::String const & line, MeshWheel& mesh_wheel, int braking, int propulsion, char side_char)
1932 {
1933  // Axle rigidity node (9999 = null)
1934  if (mesh_wheel.rigidity_node.IsValidAnyState() && mesh_wheel.rigidity_node.Num() == 9999)
1935  {
1936  mesh_wheel.rigidity_node.Invalidate();
1937  }
1938 
1939  if (braking < 0 || braking > 4)
1940  {
1941  this->AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid value of parameter ~7 (braking), using 0 (no braking)");
1942  braking = 0;
1943  }
1944  mesh_wheel.braking = Wheels::Braking(braking);
1945 
1946  if (propulsion < 0 || propulsion > 2)
1947  {
1948  this->AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid value of parameter ~8 (propulsion), using 0 (no propulsion)");
1949  braking = 0;
1950  }
1951  mesh_wheel.propulsion = Wheels::Propulsion(propulsion);
1952 
1953  mesh_wheel.side = MeshWheel::SIDE_RIGHT;
1954  if (side_char != 'r')
1955  {
1956  if (side_char != 'l')
1957  {
1958  this->AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, std::string("Invalid SIDE flag (acceptable are [r/l]), parsing as LEFT for backwards compatibility: ") + side_char);
1959  }
1960  mesh_wheel.side = MeshWheel::SIDE_LEFT;
1961  }
1962 
1963  if (m_sequential_importer.IsEnabled())
1964  {
1965  m_sequential_importer.GenerateNodesForWheel(File::KEYWORD_MESHWHEELS, mesh_wheel.num_rays, mesh_wheel.rigidity_node.IsValidAnyState());
1966  }
1967 
1968  m_current_module->mesh_wheels.push_back(mesh_wheel);
1969 }
1970 
1971 void Parser::ParseMeshWheelUnsafe(Ogre::String const & line)
1972 {
1973  PARSE_UNSAFE(line, 16,
1974  {
1975  MeshWheel mesh_wheel;
1976  mesh_wheel.node_defaults = m_user_node_defaults;
1977  mesh_wheel.beam_defaults = m_user_beam_defaults;
1978 
1979  mesh_wheel.tyre_radius = STR_PARSE_REAL(values[ 0]);
1980  mesh_wheel.rim_radius = STR_PARSE_REAL(values[ 1]);
1981  mesh_wheel.width = STR_PARSE_REAL(values[ 2]);
1982  mesh_wheel.num_rays = STR_PARSE_INT (values[ 3]);

2096 
2097 void Parser::VerifyAndProcessMeshWheel2(Ogre::String const & line, MeshWheel2& mesh_wheel_2, int braking, int propulsion, char side_char)
2098 {
2099  // Axle rigidity node (9999 = null)
2100  if (mesh_wheel_2.rigidity_node.IsValidAnyState() && mesh_wheel_2.rigidity_node.Num() == 9999)
2101  {
2102  mesh_wheel_2.rigidity_node.Invalidate();
2103  }
2104 
2105  if (braking < 0 || braking > 4)
2106  {
2107  this->AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid value of parameter ~7 (braking), using 0 (no braking)");
2108  braking = 0;
2109  }
2110  mesh_wheel_2.braking = Wheels::Braking(braking);
2111 
2112  if (propulsion < 0 || propulsion > 2)
2113  {
2114  this->AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid value of parameter ~8 (propulsion), using 0 (no propulsion)");
2115  braking = 0;
2116  }
2117  mesh_wheel_2.propulsion = Wheels::Propulsion(propulsion);
2118 
2119  mesh_wheel_2.side = MeshWheel::SIDE_RIGHT;
2120  if (side_char != 'r')
2121  {
2122  if (side_char != 'l')
2123  {
2124  this->AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, std::string("Invalid SIDE flag (acceptable are [r/l]), parsing as LEFT for backwards compatibility: ") + side_char);
2125  }
2126  mesh_wheel_2.side = MeshWheel::SIDE_LEFT;
2127  }
2128 
2129  if (m_sequential_importer.IsEnabled())
2130  {
2131  m_sequential_importer.GenerateNodesForWheel(File::KEYWORD_MESHWHEELS2, mesh_wheel_2.num_rays, mesh_wheel_2.rigidity_node.IsValidAnyState());
2132  }
2133 
2134  m_current_module->mesh_wheels_2.push_back(mesh_wheel_2);
2135 }

2137 void Parser::ParseHook(Ogre::String const & line)
2138 {
2139  boost::smatch results;
2140  if (! boost::regex_search(line, results, Regexes::SECTION_HOOKS))
2141  {
2142  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid line, ignoring...");
2143  return;
2144  }
2145  /* NOTE: Positions in 'results' array match E_CAPTURE*() positions (starting with 1) in the respective regex. */
2146 
2147  Hook hook;
2148  hook.node = _ParseNodeRef(results[1]);
2149 
2150  Ogre::StringVector tokens = Ogre::StringUtil::split(results[2], ",");
2151  Ogre::StringVector::iterator iter = tokens.begin();
2152  for ( ; iter != tokens.end(); iter++)
2153  {
2154  boost::smatch results;
2155  if (! boost::regex_search(*iter, results, Regexes::HOOKS_OPTIONS))
2156  {
2157  AddMessage(*iter, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid option of 'hooks', ignoring...");
2158  return;
2159  }
2160 
2161  if (! results[1].matched)
2162  {
2163  AddMessage(*iter, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid option of 'hooks', ignoring...");
2164  return;
2165  }
2166  else if (results[2].matched)
2167  {
2168  BITMASK_SET_1(hook.flags, Hook::FLAG_SELF_LOCK);
2169  }
2170  else if (results[3].matched)
2171  {
2172  BITMASK_SET_1(hook.flags, Hook::FLAG_AUTO_LOCK);
2173  }
2174  else if (results[4].matched)
2175  {
2176  BITMASK_SET_1(hook.flags, Hook::FLAG_NO_DISABLE);
2177  }
2178  else if (results[5].matched)
2179  {
2180  BITMASK_SET_1(hook.flags, Hook::FLAG_NO_ROPE);
2181  }
2182  else if (results[6].matched)
2183  {
2184  BITMASK_SET_1(hook.flags, Hook::FLAG_VISIBLE);
2185  }
2186  else if (results[7].matched)
2187  {
2188  hook.option_hook_range = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[8]);
2189  }
2190  else if (results[9].matched)
2191  {
2192  hook.option_max_force = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[10]);
2193  }
2194  else if (results[11].matched)
2195  {
2196  hook.option_hookgroup = STR_PARSE_INT(results[12]);
2197  }
2198  else if (results[13].matched)
2199  {
2200  hook.option_lockgroup = STR_PARSE_INT(results[14]);
2201  }
2202  else if (results[15].matched)
2203  {
2204  hook.option_timer = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[16]);
2205  }
2206  else if (results[17].matched)
2207  {
2208  hook.option_minimum_range_meters = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[18]);
2209  }
2210  else if (results[19].matched)
2211  {
2212  hook.option_speed_coef = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[20]);
2213  }
2214  }
2215 
2216  m_current_module->hooks.push_back(hook);
2217 }

2237 void Parser::ParseGuiSettings(Ogre::String const & line)
2238 {
2239  boost::smatch results;
2240  if (! boost::regex_search(line, results, Regexes::SECTION_GUISETTINGS))
2241  {
2242  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid line, ignoring...");
2243  return;
2244  }
2245  /* NOTE: Positions in 'results' array match E_CAPTURE*() positions (starting with 1) in the respective regex. */
2246

2248  {

2250  }

2254  }
2255  else if (results[7].matched)
2256  {
2257  m_current_module->gui_settings->speedo_highest_kph = STR_PARSE_INT(results[7]);

2260  {

2262  if ( input != 0 && input != 1 ) // This is backwards compatible, legacy check was: 1. parse VALUE_STR as int 2. compare (VALUE_INT == 1)
2263  {
2264  std::stringstream msg;
2265  msg << "Param 'Use Max RPM' has invalid value '" << results[9] << "'. Valid values are '0' (no) or '1' (yes). Parsing as '0' (no). Please fix.";
2266  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, msg.str());
2267  }

2269  }
2270  else if (results[11].matched)
2271  {
2272  m_current_module->gui_settings->help_material = results[11];
2273  }
2274  else if (results[12].matched)
2275  {
2276  if (results[14].matched)
2277  {

2279  }

2282  m_current_module->gui_settings->interactive_overview_map_mode = GuiSettings::MAP_MODE_SIMPLE;
2283  }
2284  else if (results[16].matched)
2285  {
2286  m_current_module->gui_settings->interactive_overview_map_mode = GuiSettings::MAP_MODE_ZOOM;
2287  }
2288  }
2289  else if (results[18].matched)
2290  {
2291  m_current_module->gui_settings->dashboard_layouts.push_back(results[18]);
2292  }
2293  else if (results[20].matched)
2294  {
2295  m_current_module->gui_settings->rtt_dashboard_layouts.push_back(results[20]);
2296  }
2297  else
2298  {
2299  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid line, ignoring...");
2300  }
2301 }

2432 unsigned int Parser::_ParseCabOptions(Ogre::String const & options_str)
2433 {
2434  unsigned int cab_options = 0;
2435  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < options_str.length(); i++)
2436  {
2437  switch (options_str.at(i))
2438  {
2439  case 'c':
2440  cab_options |= Cab::OPTION_c_CONTACT;
2441  break;
2442  case 'b':
2443  cab_options |= Cab::OPTION_b_BUOYANT;
2444  break;
2445  case 'D':
2446  cab_options |= (Cab::OPTION_c_CONTACT | Cab::OPTION_b_BUOYANT);
2447  break;
2448  case 'p':
2449  cab_options |= Cab::OPTION_p_10xTOUGHER;
2450  break;
2451  case 'u':
2452  cab_options |= Cab::OPTION_u_INVULNERABLE;
2453  break;
2454  case 'F':
2455  cab_options |= (Cab::OPTION_p_10xTOUGHER | Cab::OPTION_b_BUOYANT);
2456  break;
2457  case 'S':
2458  cab_options |= (Cab::OPTION_u_INVULNERABLE | Cab::OPTION_b_BUOYANT);
2459  break;
2460  case 'n':
2461  break; /* Placeholder, does nothing */
2462 
2463  default:
2464  std::stringstream msg;
2465  msg << "Subsection 'submesh/cab': Invalid option '" << options_str.at(i) << "', ignoring...";
2466  this->AddMessage(options_str, Message::TYPE_WARNING, msg.str());
2467  break;
2468  }
2469  }
2470  return cab_options;
2471 }
2472 
2473 bool Parser::_TryParseCab(Ogre::String const & line)
2474 {
2475  boost::smatch results;
2476  if (! boost::regex_search(line, results, Regexes::SUBMESH_SUBSECTION_CAB))
2477  {
2478  return false;
2479  }
2480  /* NOTE: Positions in 'results' array match E_CAPTURE*() positions (starting with 1) in the respective regex. */
2481 
2482  Cab cab;
2483  cab.nodes[0] = _ParseNodeRef(results[1]);
2484  cab.nodes[1] = _ParseNodeRef(results[3]);
2485  cab.nodes[2] = _ParseNodeRef(results[5]);
2486 
2487  if (results[6].matched)
2488  {
2489  cab.options = this->_ParseCabOptions(results[8].str());
2490  }
2491 
2492  m_current_submesh->cab_triangles.push_back(cab);
2493  return true;
2494 }
2495 
2496 void Parser::ParseSubmeshUnsafe(Ogre::String const & line)
2497 {
2498  if (m_current_subsection == File::SUBSECTION__SUBMESH__CAB)
2499  {
2500  PARSE_UNSAFE(line, 3,
2501  {
2502  Cab cab;
2503  cab.nodes[0] = this->_ParseNodeRef(values[0]);
2504  cab.nodes[1] = this->_ParseNodeRef(values[1]);
2505  cab.nodes[2] = this->_ParseNodeRef(values[2]);
2506  if (values.size() > 3)
2507  {
2508  cab.options = this->_ParseCabOptions(values[3]);
2509  }
2510 
2511  m_current_submesh->cab_triangles.push_back(cab);
2512  });
2513  }
2514  else if (m_current_subsection == File::SUBSECTION__SUBMESH__TEXCOORDS)
2515  {
2516  PARSE_UNSAFE(line, 3,
2517  {
2518  Texcoord texcoord;
2519  texcoord.node = this->_ParseNodeRef(values[0]);
2520  texcoord.u = STR_PARSE_REAL(values[1]);
2521  texcoord.v = STR_PARSE_REAL(values[2]);
2522 
2523  m_current_submesh->texcoords.push_back(texcoord);
2524  });
2525  }
2526 }
2527 
2528 void Parser::ParseSubmesh(Ogre::String const & line)
2529 {
2530  if (m_current_subsection == File::SUBSECTION__SUBMESH__CAB)
2531  {
2532  if (!this->_TryParseCab(line))
2533  {
2534  this->ParseSubmeshUnsafe(line);
2535  }
2536  }
2537  else if (m_current_subsection == File::SUBSECTION__SUBMESH__TEXCOORDS)
2538  {
2539  boost::smatch results;
2540  if (! boost::regex_search(line, results, Regexes::SUBMESH_SUBSECTION_TEXCOORDS))
2541  {
2542  this->ParseSubmeshUnsafe(line);
2543  return;
2544  }
2545  /* NOTE: Positions in 'results' array match E_CAPTURE*() positions (starting with 1) in the respective regex. */
2546 
2547  Texcoord texcoord;
2548  texcoord.node = _ParseNodeRef(results[1]);
2549  texcoord.u = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[2]);
2550  texcoord.v = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[3]);
2551 
2552  m_current_submesh->texcoords.push_back(texcoord);
2553  }
2554  // Experiment, left here for future use
2555  //else if (this->_TryParseCab(line))
2556  //{
2557  // AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, "Section submesh has no subsection defined, but subsequent line matches 'cab' entry. Parsed as 'cab'.");
2558  //}
2559  else
2560  {
2561  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Section submesh has no subsection defined, line not parsed.");
2562  }
2563 }
2564 
2565 void Parser::_ImportLegacyFlexbodyForsetLine(Ogre::String const & line)
2566 {
2567  // "forset" keyword is obsolete in fileformatversion >= 450
2568  // This code is import-only
2569 
2570  boost::smatch line_results;
2571  if (! boost::regex_search(line, line_results, Regexes::FLEXBODIES_SUBSECTION_FORSET_LINE))
2572  {
2573  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid line, ignoring...");
2574  return;
2575  }
2576 
2577  Ogre::StringVector tokens = Ogre::StringUtil::split(line_results[2], ",");
2578  // NOTE: This splitting process silently ignores duplicate comma ",,". Empty string element is not generated.
2579  auto itor = tokens.begin();
2580  auto end = tokens.end();
2581  for ( ; itor != end; ++itor)
2582  {
2583  unsigned noderef_flags = Node::Ref::IMPORT_STATE_IS_VALID;
2584  boost::smatch results;
2585  if (! boost::regex_search(*itor, results, Regexes::FORSET_ELEMENT))
2586  {
2587  /* Invalid element, attempt to parse as node number for backwards compatibility */
2588  unsigned int result = strtoul((*itor).c_str(), nullptr, 10);
2589  std::stringstream msg;
2590  msg << "Subsection 'forset': Invalid element '" << *itor << "', parsing as '" << result << "' for backwards compatibility. Please fix.";
2591  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, msg.str());
2592 
2593  m_last_flexbody->node_list_to_import.push_back(Node::Range(Node::Ref(TOSTRING(result), result, noderef_flags, m_current_line_number)));
2594  }
2595  else if (results[1].matched) /* Range of numbered nodes */
2596  {
2597  int start_node_index = STR_PARSE_INT(results[2]);
2598  int end_node_index = STR_PARSE_INT(results[3]);
2599  m_last_flexbody->node_list_to_import.push_back(
2600  Node::Range(
2601  Node::Ref(results[2], static_cast<unsigned>(start_node_index), noderef_flags, m_current_line_number),
2602  Node::Ref(results[3], static_cast<unsigned>(end_node_index), noderef_flags, m_current_line_number)));
2603  }
2604  else if(results[4].matched) /* Single numbered node */
2605  {
2606  int node_index = STR_PARSE_INT(results[4]);
2607  m_last_flexbody->node_list_to_import.push_back(Node::Range(Node::Ref(results[4], static_cast<unsigned>(node_index), noderef_flags, m_current_line_number)));
2608  }
2609  }
2610 }

2612 void Parser::ParseFlexbody(Ogre::String const & line)
2613 {
2614  if (m_current_subsection == File::SUBSECTION__FLEXBODIES__PROPLIKE_LINE)
2615  {
2616  boost::smatch results;
2617  if (! boost::regex_search(line, results, Regexes::FLEXBODIES_SUBSECTION_PROPLIKE_LINE))
2618  {
2619  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid line, ignoring...");
2620  return;
2621  }
2622  /* NOTE: Positions in 'results' array match E_CAPTURE*() positions (starting with 1) in the respective regex. */
2623 
2624  Flexbody flexbody;
2625  flexbody.reference_node = _ParseNodeRef(results[1]);
2626  flexbody.x_axis_node = _ParseNodeRef(results[3]);
2627  flexbody.y_axis_node = _ParseNodeRef(results[5]);
2628 
2629  flexbody.offset.x = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[7]);
2630  flexbody.offset.y = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[9]);
2631  flexbody.offset.z = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[11]);
2632 
2633  flexbody.rotation.x = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[13]);
2634  flexbody.rotation.y = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[15]);
2635  flexbody.rotation.z = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[17]);
2636 
2637  flexbody.mesh_name = results[19];
2638 
2639  m_last_flexbody = boost::shared_ptr<Flexbody>( new Flexbody(flexbody) );
2640  m_current_module->flexbodies.push_back(m_last_flexbody);
2641 
2642  /* Switch subsection */
2643  m_current_subsection = File::SUBSECTION__FLEXBODIES__FORSET_LINE;
2644  }
2645  else if (m_current_subsection == File::SUBSECTION__FLEXBODIES__FORSET_LINE)
2646  {
2647  this->_ImportLegacyFlexbodyForsetLine(line);
2648 
2649  /* Switch subsection */
2650  m_current_subsection = File::SUBSECTION__FLEXBODIES__PROPLIKE_LINE;
2651  }
2652  else
2653  {
2654  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_FATAL_ERROR, "Internal parser failure, section 'flexbodies' not parsed.");
2655  }

2740  {
2741  flare.blink_delay_milis = STR_PARSE_INT(results[32]);

3124 void Parser::ParseDirectiveAddAnimation(Ogre::String const & line)
3125 {
3126  assert(m_current_module != nullptr);
3127 
3128  if (m_current_module->props.size() == 0)
3129  {
3130  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Directive 'add_animation' has no prop to animate, ignoring...");
3131  return;
3132  }
3133 
3134  boost::smatch results;
3135  if (! boost::regex_search(line, results, Regexes::DIRECTIVE_ADD_ANIMATION))
3136  {
3137  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid directive 'add_animation', ignoring...");
3138  return;
3139  }
3140  /* NOTE: Positions in 'results' array match E_CAPTURE*() positions (starting with 1) in the respective regex. */
3141 
3142  Animation animation;
3143  animation.ratio = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[4]);
3144  animation.lower_limit = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[8]);
3145  animation.upper_limit = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[12]);
3146 
3147  Ogre::StringVector tokens = Ogre::StringUtil::split(results[16], ",");
3148 
3149  for (Ogre::StringVector::iterator itor = tokens.begin(); itor != tokens.end(); itor++)
3150  {
3151  boost::smatch token_results;
3152  if (! boost::regex_search(*itor, token_results, Regexes::IDENTIFY_ADD_ANIMATION_TOKEN))
3153  {
3154  std::stringstream msg;
3155  msg << "Directive 'add_animation': Unrecognized/misplaced token '" << *itor << "', ignoring....";
3156  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, msg.str());
3157  continue;
3158  }
3159 
3160  /* NOTE: Positions in 'token_results' array match E_CAPTURE*() positions (starting with 1) in Regexes::IDENTIFY_ADD_ANIMATION_TOKEN. */
3161 
3162  if (token_results[2].matched) /* autoanimate */
3163  {
3164  BITMASK_SET_1(animation.mode, Animation::MODE_AUTO_ANIMATE);
3165  }
3166  else if (token_results[3].matched) /* noflip */
3167  {
3168  BITMASK_SET_1(animation.mode, Animation::MODE_NO_FLIP);
3169  }
3170  else if (token_results[4].matched) /* bounce */
3171  {
3172  BITMASK_SET_1(animation.mode, Animation::MODE_BOUNCE);
3173  }
3174  else if (token_results[5].matched) /* eventlock */
3175  {
3176  BITMASK_SET_1(animation.mode, Animation::MODE_EVENT_LOCK);
3177  }
3178  else if (token_results[6].matched) /* Mode */
3179  {
3180  if (! token_results[7].matched)
3181  {
3182  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Directive 'add_animation': Token 'mode' has invalid format, skipping....");
3183  continue;
3184  }
3185  else
3186  {
3187  _ParseDirectiveAddAnimationMode(animation, token_results[8]);
3188  }
3189  }
3190  else if (token_results[9].matched) /* Source */
3191  {
3192  if (! token_results[10].matched)
3193  {
3194  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Directive 'add_animation': Token 'source' has invalid format, skipping....");
3195  continue;
3196  }
3197  else
3198  {
3199  _ParseDirectiveAddAnimationSource(animation, token_results[11]);
3200  }
3201  }
3202  else if (token_results[12].matched) /* Event */
3203  {
3204  if (! token_results[13].matched)
3205  {
3206  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Directive 'add_animation': Token 'event' has invalid format, skipping....");
3207  continue;
3208  }
3209  else
3210  {
3211  animation.event = token_results[14];
3212  }
3213  }
3214  else
3215  {
3216  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "[Internal error] Directive 'add_animation': Token '" + *itor + "' passed syntax check, but wasn't recognized....");
3217  }
3218  }
3219 
3220  m_current_module->props.back().animations.push_back(animation);
3221 }

3400 void Parser::ParseEngine(Ogre::String const & line)
3401 {
3402  boost::smatch results;
3403  if (! boost::regex_search(line, results, Regexes::SECTION_ENGINE))
3404  {
3405  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid line, ignoring...");
3406  return;
3407  }
3408  /* NOTE: Positions in 'results' array match E_CAPTURE*() positions (starting with 1) in the respective regex. */
3409 
3410  Engine engine;
3411  engine.shift_down_rpm = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[1]);
3412  engine.shift_up_rpm = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[3]);
3413  engine.torque = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[5]);
3414  engine.global_gear_ratio = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[7]);
3415  engine.reverse_gear_ratio = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[9]);
3416  engine.neutral_gear_ratio = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[11]);
3417 
3418  /* Forward gears */
3419  bool terminator_found = false;
3420  for (unsigned int gear_index = 0; gear_index < 21; ++gear_index)
3421  {
3422  unsigned int result_index = 13 + (gear_index * 3);
3423 
3424  if (results[result_index].matched)
3425  {
3426  float value = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[result_index]);
3427  if (value <= 0.f)
3428  {
3429  terminator_found = true;
3430  break;
3431  }
3432  engine.gear_ratios.push_back(value);
3433  }
3434  else
3435  {
3436  break;
3437  }
3438  }
3439 
3440  if (engine.gear_ratios.size() == 0)
3441  {
3442  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Engine has no forward gear, ignoring...");
3443  return;
3444  }
3445 
3446  if (! terminator_found && ! results[42].matched) /* Terminator, required, absence tolerated for compatibility */
3447  {
3448  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, "Forward gears list is not terminated using '-1.0'. Please fix.");
3449  }
3450 
3451  m_current_module->engine = boost::shared_ptr<Engine>( new Engine(engine) );
3452 }

3477 void Parser::_ParseSectionsCommandsCommands2(Ogre::String const & line, boost::regex const & regex, unsigned int format_version)
3478 {
3479  boost::smatch results;
3480  if (! boost::regex_search(line, results, regex))
3481  {
3482  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid line, ignoring...");
3483  return;
3484  }
3485  /* NOTE: Positions in 'results' array match E_CAPTURE*() positions (starting with 1) in the respective regex. */
3486 
3487  Command2 command2;
3488  command2.beam_defaults = m_user_beam_defaults;
3489  command2.detacher_group = m_current_detacher_group;
3490  command2._format_version = format_version;
3491  command2.inertia_defaults = m_user_default_inertia;
3492  command2.nodes[0] = _ParseNodeRef(results[1]);
3493  command2.nodes[1] = _ParseNodeRef(results[3]);
3494 
3495  /* Shorten/lenghten rate */
3496  command2.shorten_rate = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[5]);
3497  unsigned int result_index;
3498  if (format_version == 2)
3499  {
3500  command2.lengthen_rate = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[7]);
3501  result_index = 9;
3502  }
3503  else
3504  {
3505  command2.lengthen_rate = command2.shorten_rate;
3506  result_index = 7;
3507  }
3508 
3509  command2.max_contraction = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[result_index]);
3510  result_index +=2;
3511  command2.max_extension = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[result_index]);
3512  result_index +=2;
3513  command2.contract_key = STR_PARSE_INT(results[result_index]);
3514  result_index +=2;
3515  command2.extend_key = STR_PARSE_INT(results[result_index]);
3516 
3517  /* Options */
3518  result_index += 3;
3519  if (results[result_index].matched)
3520  {
3521  std::string options_str = results[result_index].str();
3522  bool centering = false;
3523  bool one_press_mode = false;
3524  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < options_str.length(); i++)
3525  {
3526  const char c = options_str.at(i);
3527  switch(c)
3528  {
3529  case 'n': /* Filler */
3530  break;
3531 
3532  case 'i':
3533  command2.options |= Command2::OPTION_i_INVISIBLE;
3534  break;
3535 
3536  case 'r':
3537  command2.options |= Command2::OPTION_r_ROPE;
3538  break;
3539 
3540  case 'c':
3541  if (! one_press_mode)
3542  {
3543  command2.options |= Command2::OPTION_c_AUTO_CENTER;
3544  centering = true;
3545  }
3546  else
3547  {
3548  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, "Command cannot be one-pressed and self centering at the same time, ignoring flag 'c'");
3549  }
3550  break;
3551 
3552  case 'f':
3553  command2.options |= Command2::OPTION_f_NOT_FASTER;
3554  break;
3555 
3556  case 'p':
3557  if (centering)
3558  {
3559  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, "Command cannot be one-pressed and self centering at the same time, ignoring flag 'p'");
3560  }
3561  else if (one_press_mode)
3562  {
3563  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, "Command already has a one-pressed c.mode, ignoring flag 'p'");
3564  }
3565  else
3566  {
3567  command2.options |= Command2::OPTION_p_PRESS_ONCE;
3568  one_press_mode = true;
3569  }
3570  break;
3571 
3572  case 'o':
3573  if (centering)
3574  {
3575  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, "Command cannot be one-pressed and self centering at the same time, ignoring flag 'o'");
3576  }
3577  else if (one_press_mode)
3578  {
3579  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, "Command already has a one-pressed c.mode, ignoring flag 'o'");
3580  }
3581  else
3582  {
3583  command2.options |= Command2::OPTION_o_PRESS_ONCE_CENTER;
3584  one_press_mode = true;
3585  }
3586  break;
3587 
3588  default:
3589  this->AddMessage(options_str, Message::TYPE_WARNING, std::string("Ignoring invalid option: ") + c);
3590  break;
3591  }
3592  }
3593 
3594  result_index += 3;
3595  if (results[result_index].matched)
3596  {
3597  command2.description = results[result_index];
3598 
3599  if (format_version == 1)
3600  {
3601  result_index += 5;
3602  if (_ParseOptionalInertia(command2.inertia, results, result_index))
3603  {
3604  result_index += 12;
3605 
3606  if (results[result_index].matched)
3607  {
3608  command2.affect_engine = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[result_index]);
3609 
3610  result_index += 3;
3611  if (results[result_index].matched)
3612  {
3613  command2.needs_engine = STR_PARSE_BOOL(results[result_index]);
3614  }
3615  }
3616  }
3617  }
3618  else if (format_version == 2)
3619  {
3620  result_index += 3;
3621  if (results[result_index].matched)
3622  {
3623  std::string rest_of_line = results[result_index];
3624  boost::smatch rest_of_results;
3625  result_index = 0;
3626  if (boost::regex_search(rest_of_line, rest_of_results, Regexes::SECTION_COMMANDS2_INERTIA_ENGINE_PART))
3627  {
3628  if (_ParseOptionalInertia(command2.inertia, rest_of_results, 2))
3629  {
3630  result_index += 12;
3631 
3632  if (rest_of_results[result_index].matched)
3633  {
3634  command2.affect_engine = STR_PARSE_REAL(rest_of_results[result_index]);
3635 
3636  result_index += 3;
3637  if (rest_of_results[result_index].matched)
3638  {
3639  command2.needs_engine = STR_PARSE_BOOL(rest_of_results[result_index]);
3640  }
3641  }
3642  }
3643  }
3644  else
3645  {
3646  Ogre::StringUtil::trim(rest_of_line);
3647  if (! rest_of_line.empty()) // Could happen with invalid trailing delimiter and I don't want to look like an idiot
3648  {
3649  std::stringstream msg;
3650  msg << "Please remove: Invalid string after parameter \"description\": \"" << rest_of_line << "\"";
3651  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, msg.str());
3652  }
3653  }
3654  }
3655  }
3656  }
3657  }
3658 
3659  m_current_module->commands_2.push_back(command2);
3660 }

3768 void Parser::ParseAxles(Ogre::String const & line)
3769 {
3770  Axle axle;
3771 
3772  Ogre::StringVector tokens = Ogre::StringUtil::split(line, ",");
3773  Ogre::StringVector::iterator iter = tokens.begin();
3774  for ( ; iter != tokens.end(); iter++)
3775  {
3776  boost::smatch results;
3777  if (! boost::regex_search(*iter, results, Regexes::SECTION_AXLES_PROPERTY))
3778  {
3779  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid property, ignoring whole line...");
3780  return;
3781  }
3782  /* NOTE: Positions in 'results' array match E_CAPTURE*() positions (starting with 1) in the respective regex. */
3783 
3784  if (results[1].matched)
3785  {
3786  unsigned int wheel_index = STR_PARSE_INT(results[2]) - 1;
3787  axle.wheels[wheel_index][0] = _ParseNodeRef(results[3]);
3788  axle.wheels[wheel_index][1] = _ParseNodeRef(results[4]);
3789  }
3790  else if (results[5].matched)
3791  {
3792  std::string options_str = results[6].str();
3793  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < options_str.length(); i++)
3794  {
3795  switch(options_str.at(i))
3796  {
3797  case 'o':
3798  axle.options.push_back(Axle::OPTION_o_OPEN);
3799  break;
3800  case 'l':
3801  axle.options.push_back(Axle::OPTION_l_LOCKED);
3802  break;
3803  case 's':
3804  axle.options.push_back(Axle::OPTION_s_SPLIT);
3805  break;
3806 
3807  default: /* No check needed, regex takes care of that */
3808  break;
3809  }
3810  }
3811  }
3812  }
3813 
3814  m_current_module->axles.push_back(axle);
3815 }

3981 void Parser::ParseTriggers(Ogre::String const & line)
3982 {
3983  boost::smatch results;
3984  if (! boost::regex_search(line, results, Regexes::SECTION_TRIGGERS))
3985  {
3986  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid line, ignoring...");
3987  return;
3988  }
3989  /* NOTE: Positions in 'results' array match E_CAPTURE*() positions (starting with 1) in the respective regex. */
3990 
3991  Trigger trigger;
3992  trigger.beam_defaults = m_user_beam_defaults;
3993  trigger.detacher_group = m_current_detacher_group;
3994  trigger.nodes[0] = _ParseNodeRef(results[1]);
3995  trigger.nodes[1] = _ParseNodeRef(results[2]);
3996  trigger.contraction_trigger_limit = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[3]);
3997  trigger.expansion_trigger_limit = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[4]);
3998  int shortbound_trigger_action = STR_PARSE_INT(results[5]);
3999  int longbound_trigger_action = STR_PARSE_INT(results[6]);
4000 
4001  if (results[8].matched)
4002  {
4003  std::string options_str = results[8].str();
4004  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < options_str.length(); i++)
4005  {
4006  switch(options_str.at(i))
4007  {
4008  case 'i':
4009  trigger.options |= Trigger::OPTION_i_INVISIBLE;
4010  break;
4011  case 'c':
4012  trigger.options |= Trigger::OPTION_c_COMMAND_STYLE;
4013  break;
4014  case 'x':
4015  trigger.options |= Trigger::OPTION_x_START_OFF;
4016  break;
4017  case 'b':
4018  trigger.options |= Trigger::OPTION_b_BLOCK_KEYS;
4019  break;
4020  case 'B':
4021  trigger.options |= Trigger::OPTION_B_BLOCK_TRIGGERS;
4022  break;
4023  case 'A':
4024  trigger.options |= Trigger::OPTION_A_INV_BLOCK_TRIGGERS;
4025  break;
4026  case 's':
4027  trigger.options |= Trigger::OPTION_s_SWITCH_CMD_NUM;
4028  break;
4029  case 'h':
4030  trigger.options |= Trigger::OPTION_h_UNLOCK_HOOKGROUPS_KEY;
4031  break;
4032  case 'H':
4033  trigger.options |= Trigger::OPTION_H_LOCK_HOOKGROUPS_KEY;
4034  break;
4035  case 't':
4036  trigger.options |= Trigger::OPTION_t_CONTINUOUS;
4037  break;
4038  case 'E':
4039  trigger.options |= Trigger::OPTION_E_ENGINE_TRIGGER;
4040  break;
4041 
4042  default:
4043  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, Ogre::String("Invalid trigger option: " + options_str.at(i)));
4044  break;
4045  }
4046  }
4047  }
4048  if (results[10].matched)
4049  {
4050  trigger.boundary_timer = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[10]);
4051  }
4052 
4053  // Handle actions
4054  if (!trigger.IsTriggerBlockerAnyType() && !trigger.IsHookToggleTrigger() && !trigger.HasFlag_E_EngineTrigger())
4055  {
4056  Trigger::CommandKeyTrigger command_keys;
4057  command_keys.contraction_trigger_key = shortbound_trigger_action;
4058  command_keys.extension_trigger_key = longbound_trigger_action;
4059  trigger.SetCommandKeyTrigger(command_keys);
4060  }
4061  else if (!trigger.IsHookToggleTrigger() && !trigger.HasFlag_E_EngineTrigger())
4062  {
4063  Trigger::HookToggleTrigger hook_toggle;
4064  hook_toggle.contraction_trigger_hookgroup_id = shortbound_trigger_action;
4065  hook_toggle.extension_trigger_hookgroup_id = longbound_trigger_action;
4066  trigger.SetHookToggleTrigger(hook_toggle);
4067  }
4068  else if (trigger.HasFlag_E_EngineTrigger())
4069  {
4070  Trigger::EngineTrigger engine_trigger;
4071  engine_trigger.function = Trigger::EngineTrigger::Function(shortbound_trigger_action);
4072  engine_trigger.motor_index = longbound_trigger_action;
4073  trigger.SetEngineTrigger(engine_trigger);
4074  }
4075 
4076 
4077  m_current_module->triggers.push_back(trigger);
4078 }

4178 void Parser::ParseSoundsources2(Ogre::String const & line)

4205  {

4209  return;
4210  }
4211  soundsource2.mode = SoundSource2::Mode(mode);
4212  }
4213  else

4215  soundsource2.mode = SoundSource2::MODE_CINECAM;
4216  soundsource2.cinecam_index = mode;
4217  }
4218

4220 
4221  m_current_module->soundsources2.push_back(soundsource2);

4224 void Parser::ParseSlidenodes(Ogre::String const & line)
4225 {
4226  boost::smatch results;
4227  if (! boost::regex_search(line, results, Regexes::SECTION_SLIDENODES))
4228  {
4229  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid line, ignoring...");
4230  return;
4231  }
4232  /* NOTE: Positions in 'results' array match E_CAPTURE*() positions (starting with 1) in the respective regex. */
4233 
4234  SlideNode slidenode;
4235  slidenode.slide_node = _ParseNodeRef(results[1]);
4236 
4237  bool in_rail_node_list = true;
4238  Ogre::StringVector tokens = Ogre::StringUtil::split(results[2], ",");
4239  for (Ogre::StringVector::iterator itor = tokens.begin(); itor != tokens.end(); ++itor)
4240  {
4241  boost::smatch token_results;
4242  if (boost::regex_search(*itor, token_results, Regexes::SLIDENODES_IDENTIFY_OPTION))
4243  {
4244  in_rail_node_list = false;
4245 
4246  if (token_results[1].matched)
4247  {
4248  slidenode.spring_rate = STR_PARSE_REAL(token_results[2]);
4249  }
4250  else if (token_results[3].matched)
4251  {
4252  slidenode.break_force = STR_PARSE_REAL(token_results[4]);
4253  slidenode._break_force_set = true;
4254  }
4255  else if (token_results[5].matched)
4256  {
4257  slidenode.tolerance = STR_PARSE_REAL(token_results[6]);
4258  }
4259  else if (token_results[7].matched)
4260  {
4261  slidenode.attachment_rate = STR_PARSE_REAL(token_results[8]);
4262  }
4263  else if (token_results[9].matched)
4264  {
4265  slidenode.railgroup_id = STR_PARSE_INT(token_results[10]);
4266  slidenode._railgroup_id_set = true;
4267  }
4268  else if (token_results[11].matched)
4269  {
4270  slidenode.max_attachment_distance = STR_PARSE_REAL(token_results[12]);
4271  }
4272  /* #13, #14 Quantity is ignored */
4273  else if (token_results[15].matched)
4274  {
4275  char option = token_results[16].str().at(0);
4276  switch (option)
4277  {
4278  case 'a':
4279  BITMASK_SET_1(slidenode.constraint_flags, SlideNode::CONSTRAINT_ATTACH_ALL);
4280  break;
4281  case 'f':
4282  BITMASK_SET_1(slidenode.constraint_flags, SlideNode::CONSTRAINT_ATTACH_FOREIGN);
4283  break;
4284  case 's':
4285  BITMASK_SET_1(slidenode.constraint_flags, SlideNode::CONSTRAINT_ATTACH_SELF);
4286  break;
4287  case 'n':
4288  BITMASK_SET_1(slidenode.constraint_flags, SlideNode::CONSTRAINT_ATTACH_NONE);
4289  break;
4290  default:
4291  this->AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, std::string("Ignoring invalid option: ") + option);
4292  break;
4293  }
4294  }
4295  }
4296  else
4297  {
4298  if (in_rail_node_list)
4299  {
4300  slidenode.rail_node_ranges.push_back( _ParseNodeRef(*itor));
4301  }
4302  else
4303  {
4304  std::stringstream msg;
4305  msg << "Invalid token: '" << *itor << "', ignoring...";
4306  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, msg.str());
4307  }
4308  }
4309  }
4310 
4311  m_current_module->slidenodes.push_back(slidenode);
4312 }

4378 unsigned int Parser::ParseShock2Options(Ogre::String const & line, std::string const & options_str)
4379 {
4380  unsigned int options = 0u;
4381  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < options_str.length(); i++)
4382  {
4383  switch (options_str.at(i))
4384  {
4385  case 'i':
4386  BITMASK_SET_1(options, Shock2::OPTION_i_INVISIBLE);
4387  break;
4388 
4389  case 'm':
4390  BITMASK_SET_1(options, Shock2::OPTION_m_METRIC);
4391  break;
4392 
4393  case 'M':
4394  BITMASK_SET_1(options, Shock2::OPTION_M_ABSOLUTE_METRIC);
4395  break;
4396 
4397  case 's':
4398  BITMASK_SET_1(options, Shock2::OPTION_s_SOFT_BUMP_BOUNDS);
4399  break;
4400 
4401  case 'n':
4402  break; // Placeholder, does nothing.
4403 
4404  default:
4405  std::stringstream msg;
4406  msg << "Invalid option: '" << options_str.at(i) << "', ignoring...";
4407  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, msg.str());
4408  break;
4409  }
4410  }
4411  return options;
4412 }

4463 unsigned int Parser::ParseShockOptions(Ogre::String const & line, std::string const & options_str)

4475  case 'R':

4477  break;

4482  break;

4485  BITMASK_SET_1(options, Shock::OPTION_m_METRIC);
4486  break;
4487 
4488  case 'n':
4489  break; // Placeholder, does nothing.
4490 
4491  default:
4492  std::stringstream msg;
4493  msg << "Invalid option: '" << options_str.at(i) << "', ignoring...";
4494  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, msg.str());
4495  break;

4498  return options;

4602 
4603 Node::Ref Parser::_ParseNodeRef(std::string const & node_id_str)
4604 {
4605  if (m_sequential_importer.IsEnabled())
4606  {
4607  // Import of legacy fileformatversion
4608  int node_id_num = STR_PARSE_INT(node_id_str);
4609  if (node_id_num < 0)
4610  {
4611  std::stringstream msg;
4612  msg << "Encountered node with illegal negative number: '" << node_id_num
4613  << "', parsing as positive '" << node_id_num * -1 << "' for backwards compatibility. Please fix as soon as possible.";
4614  AddMessage(node_id_str, Message::TYPE_WARNING, msg.str());
4615  node_id_num *= -1;
4616  }
4617  // Since fileformatversion is not known from the beginning of parsing, 2 states must be kept
4618  // at the same time: IMPORT_STATE and REGULAR_STATE. The outer logic must make the right pick.
4619  unsigned int flags = Node::Ref::IMPORT_STATE_IS_VALID | // Import state
4620  Node::Ref::REGULAR_STATE_IS_VALID | Node::Ref::REGULAR_STATE_IS_NAMED; // Regular state (fileformatversion >= 450)
4621  if (m_any_named_node_defined)
4622  {
4623  flags |= Node::Ref::IMPORT_STATE_MUST_CHECK_NAMED_FIRST;
4624  }
4625  return Node::Ref(node_id_str, node_id_num, flags, m_current_line_number);
4626  }
4627  else
4628  {
4629  // fileformatversion >= 450, use named-only nodes
4630  return Node::Ref(node_id_str, 0, Node::Ref::REGULAR_STATE_IS_VALID | Node::Ref::REGULAR_STATE_IS_NAMED, m_current_line_number);
4631  }
4632 }

4634 void Parser::ParseDirectiveSetInertiaDefaults(Ogre::String const & line)
4635 {
4636  boost::smatch results;
4637  if (! boost::regex_search(line, results, Regexes::DIRECTIVE_SET_INERTIA_DEFAULTS))
4638  {
4639  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid line, ignoring...");
4640  return;
4641  }
4642  /* NOTE: Positions in 'results' array match E_CAPTURE*() positions (starting with 1) in the respective regex. */
4643 
4644  float start_delay = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[1]);
4645  float stop_delay = 0;
4646  if (results[4].matched)
4647  {
4648  stop_delay = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[4]);
4649  }
4650  if (start_delay < 0 || stop_delay < 0)
4651  {
4652  // Reset
4653  m_user_default_inertia = m_ror_default_inertia;
4654  }
4655  else
4656  {
4657  // Create
4658  m_user_default_inertia = boost::shared_ptr<DefaultInertia>(new DefaultInertia(*m_user_default_inertia.get()));
4659 
4660  // Update
4661  m_user_default_inertia->start_delay_factor = start_delay;
4662  m_user_default_inertia->stop_delay_factor = stop_delay;
4663 
4664  if (results[7].matched)
4665  {
4666  m_user_default_inertia->start_function = results[7];
4667 
4668  if (results[10].matched)
4669  {
4670  m_user_default_inertia->stop_function = results[10];
4671  }
4672  }
4673  }
4674 
4675  if (results[11].matched)
4676  {
4677  std::stringstream msg;
4678  msg << "Illegal text after parameters: \"" << results[11] << "\", ignoring...";
4679  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, msg.str());
4680  }
4681 }

4703 void Parser::_ParseRotatorsCommon(Rotator & rotator, boost::smatch & results, unsigned int inertia_start_index)
4704 {
4705  rotator.axis_nodes[0] = _ParseNodeRef(results[1]);
4706  rotator.axis_nodes[1] = _ParseNodeRef(results[2]);
4707 
4708  rotator.base_plate_nodes[0] = _ParseNodeRef(results[3]);
4709  rotator.base_plate_nodes[1] = _ParseNodeRef(results[4]);
4710  rotator.base_plate_nodes[2] = _ParseNodeRef(results[5]);
4711  rotator.base_plate_nodes[3] = _ParseNodeRef(results[6]);
4712 
4713  rotator.rotating_plate_nodes[0] = _ParseNodeRef(results[7]);
4714  rotator.rotating_plate_nodes[1] = _ParseNodeRef(results[8]);
4715  rotator.rotating_plate_nodes[2] = _ParseNodeRef(results[9]);
4716  rotator.rotating_plate_nodes[3] = _ParseNodeRef(results[10]);
4717 
4718  rotator.rate = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[11]);
4719 
4720  rotator.spin_left_key = STR_PARSE_INT(results[12]);
4721  rotator.spin_right_key = STR_PARSE_INT(results[13]);
4722 
4723  /* Inertia part */
4724 
4725  if (_ParseOptionalInertia(rotator.inertia, results, inertia_start_index))
4726  {
4727  unsigned int i = inertia_start_index + 8;
4728 
4729  if (results[i].matched)
4730  {
4731  rotator.engine_coupling = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[i]);
4732  i += 2;
4733 
4734  if (results[i].matched)
4735  {
4736  rotator.needs_engine = STR_PARSE_BOOL(results[i]);
4737  }
4738  }
4739  }
4740 }

4810 void Parser::ParseFileinfo(Ogre::String const & line)
4811 {
4812  boost::smatch results;
4813  if (! boost::regex_search(line, results, Regexes::INLINE_SECTION_FILEINFO))
4814  {
4815  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Inline-section 'fileinfo' has invalid format, ignoring...");
4816  return;
4817  }
4818  /* NOTE: Positions in 'results' array match E_CAPTURE*() positions (starting with 1) in the respective regex. */
4819 
4820  Fileinfo fileinfo;
4821  bool go_next = false;
4822 
4823  /* UID */
4824  if (results[3].matched)
4825  {
4826  fileinfo.unique_id = results[3];
4827  fileinfo._has_unique_id = true;
4828  go_next = true;
4829  }
4830  else if (results[2].matched)
4831  {
4832  go_next = true;
4833  }
4834 
4835  if (!go_next)
4836  {
4837  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Inline-section 'fileinfo' has invalid UID, ignoring line...");
4838  }
4839  go_next = false;
4840 
4841  /* category id */
4842  if (results[6].matched)
4843  {
4844  fileinfo.category_id = STR_PARSE_INT(results[6]);
4845  fileinfo._has_category_id = true;
4846  go_next = true;
4847  }
4848  else if (results[7].matched)
4849  {
4850  go_next = true;
4851  }
4852 
4853  if (!go_next)
4854  {
4855  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Inline-section 'fileinfo' has invalid category id, ignoring line...");
4856  }
4857  go_next = false;
4858 
4859  /* file version */
4860  int version = -1;
4861  if (results[10].matched)
4862  {
4863  // Integer input
4864  version = STR_PARSE_INT(results[10]);
4865  }
4866  else if (results[11].matched)
4867  {
4868  // Float input, silently parse as int.
4869  version = STR_PARSE_INT(results[11]);
4870  }
4871 
4872  if (version >= 0)
4873  {
4874  fileinfo.file_version = static_cast<unsigned int>(version);
4875  fileinfo._has_file_version_set = true;
4876  }
4877 
4878  m_definition->file_info = boost::shared_ptr<Fileinfo>( new Fileinfo(fileinfo) );
4879 }
