4881 void Parser::ParseRopes(Ogre::String const & line)
4882 {
4883  boost::smatch results;
4884  if (! boost::regex_search(line, results, Regexes::SECTION_ROPES))
4885  {
4886  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid line, ignoring...");
4887  return;
4888  }
4889  /* NOTE: Positions in 'results' array match E_CAPTURE*() positions (starting with 1) in the respective regex. */

4892  rope.beam_defaults = m_user_beam_defaults;
4893  rope.detacher_group = m_current_detacher_group;
4894  rope.root_node = _ParseNodeRef(results[1]);
4895  rope.end_node = _ParseNodeRef(results[2]);

4897  if (results[4].matched)

4900  const char options_char = options_str.at(0);
4901  if (options_char == 'i')
4902  {

4904  rope._has_invisible_set = true;
4905  }
4906  else

4916 {
4917  boost::smatch results;
4918  if (! boost::regex_search(line, results, Regexes::SECTION_ROPABLES))
4919  {

4921  return;

4924

4926  ropable.node = _ParseNodeRef(results[1]);
4927 
4928  if (results[3].matched)
4929  {
4930  ropable.group = STR_PARSE_INT(results[3]);
4931  ropable._has_group_set = true;
4932 
4933  if (results[5].matched)
4934  {
4935  unsigned int multilock = STR_PARSE_INT(results[5]);
4936  ropable.multilock = multilock > 0;
4937  ropable._has_multilock_set = true;
4938  }
4939  }

4968 void Parser::ParseProps(Ogre::String const & line)
4969 {
4970  boost::smatch results;
4971  if (! boost::regex_search(line, results, Regexes::SECTION_PROPS))
4972  {
4973  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid line, ignoring...");
4974  return;
4975  }
4976  /* NOTE: Positions in 'results' array match E_CAPTURE*() positions (starting with 1) in the respective regex. */
4977 
4978  Prop prop;
4979  prop.reference_node = _ParseNodeRef(results[1]);
4980  prop.x_axis_node = _ParseNodeRef(results[3]);
4981  prop.y_axis_node = _ParseNodeRef(results[5]);
4982 
4983  prop.offset.x = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[7]);
4984  prop.offset.y = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[9]);
4985  prop.offset.z = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[11]);
4986 
4987  prop.rotation.x = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[13]);
4988  prop.rotation.y = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[15]);
4989  prop.rotation.z = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[17]);
4990 
4991  prop.mesh_name = results[19];
4992 
4993  /* Special props */
4994  boost::smatch special_results;
4995  if (boost::regex_search(prop.mesh_name, special_results, Regexes::SPECIAL_PROPS))
4996  {
4997  for (int i = 1; i <= 11; i++)
4998  {
4999  if (special_results[i].matched)
5000  {
5001  if (i == 3 || i == 4) /* Custom steering wheel */
5002  {
5003  prop.special = Prop::Special(i);
5004 
5005  std::string special_params = results[21];
5006  boost::smatch dashboard_results;
5007  if (boost::regex_search(special_params, dashboard_results, Regexes::SPECIAL_PROP_DASHBOARD))
5008  {
5009  if ( dashboard_results[4].matched )
5010  {
5011  prop.special_prop_steering_wheel.offset.x = STR_PARSE_REAL(dashboard_results[4]);
5012 
5013  if ( dashboard_results[7].matched )
5014  {
5015  prop.special_prop_steering_wheel.offset.y = STR_PARSE_REAL(dashboard_results[7]);
5016 
5017  if ( dashboard_results[10].matched )
5018  {
5019  prop.special_prop_steering_wheel.offset.z = STR_PARSE_REAL(dashboard_results[10]);
5020  prop.special_prop_steering_wheel._offset_is_set = true;
5021  prop.special_prop_steering_wheel.mesh_name = dashboard_results[1];
5022 
5023  if ( dashboard_results[13].matched )
5024  {
5025  prop.special_prop_steering_wheel.rotation_angle = STR_PARSE_REAL(dashboard_results[13]);
5026  }
5027  }
5028  }
5029  }
5030  }
5031  }
5032  else if (i == 9) /* Beacon */
5033  {
5034  prop.special = Prop::Special(i);
5035  std::string special_params = results[15];
5036  boost::smatch beacon_results;
5037  if (boost::regex_search(special_params, beacon_results, Regexes::SPECIAL_PROP_BEACON))
5038  {
5039  /* Flare material name */
5040  prop.special_prop_beacon.flare_material_name = beacon_results[1];
5041  Ogre::StringUtil::trim(prop.special_prop_beacon.flare_material_name);
5042  /* Color */
5043  prop.special_prop_beacon.color = Ogre::ColourValue(
5044  STR_PARSE_REAL(beacon_results[3]),
5045  STR_PARSE_REAL(beacon_results[5]),
5046  STR_PARSE_REAL(beacon_results[7])
5047  );
5048  }
5049  }
5050  else
5051  {
5052  prop.special = Prop::Special(i);
5053  }
5054  break;
5055  }
5056  }
5057  }
5058 
5059  m_current_module->props.push_back(prop);
5060 }

5124 
5125 // Static
5126 void Parser::_TrimTrailingComments(std::string const & line_in, std::string & line_out)
5127 {
5128  // Trim trailing comment
5129  // We need to handle a case of lines as [keyword 1, 2, 3 ;;///// Comment!]
5130  int comment_start = line_in.find_first_of(";");
5131  if (comment_start != Ogre::String::npos)
5132  {
5133  line_out = line_in.substr(0, comment_start);
5134  return;
5135  }
5136  // The [//Comment] is harder - the '/' character may also be present in DESCRIPTION arguments!
5137  comment_start = line_in.find_last_of("/");
5138  if (comment_start != Ogre::String::npos)
5139  {
5140  while (comment_start >= 0)
5141  {
5142  char c = line_in[comment_start - 1];
5143  if (c != '/' && c != ' ' && c != '\t')
5144  {
5145  break; // Start of comment found
5146  }
5147  --comment_start;
5148  }
5149  line_out = line_in.substr(0, comment_start);
5150  return;
5151  }
5152  // No comment found
5153  line_out = line_in;
5154 }
5155 
5156 void Parser::_ParseNodesLegacyMethod(Ogre::String line, bool is_version_2)
5157 {
5158  Ogre::StringUtil::trim(line);
5159  Ogre::StringVector args;
5160  int num_args = this->_ParseArgs(line, args, 4u);
5161  if (num_args == -1)
5162  {
5163  return; // Error already logged
5164  }
5165 
5166  Node node;
5167  node.node_defaults = m_user_node_defaults;
5168  node.beam_defaults = m_user_beam_defaults;
5169  node.detacher_group = m_current_detacher_group;
5170 
5171  if (is_version_2)
5172  {
5173  node.id.SetStr(args[0]);
5174  if (m_sequential_importer.IsEnabled())
5175  {
5176  m_sequential_importer.AddNamedNode(args[0]);
5177  }
5178  m_any_named_node_defined = true; // For import logic
5179  }
5180  else
5181  {
5182  const unsigned int node_num = static_cast<unsigned int>(STR_PARSE_INT(args[0]));
5183  node.id.SetNum(node_num);
5184  if (m_sequential_importer.IsEnabled())
5185  {
5186  m_sequential_importer.AddNumberedNode(node_num);
5187  }
5188  }
5189  node.position.x = STR_PARSE_REAL(args[1]);
5190  node.position.y = STR_PARSE_REAL(args[2]);
5191  node.position.z = STR_PARSE_REAL(args[3]);
5192 
5193  if (num_args > 4) /* Has options? */
5194  {
5195  _ParseNodeOptions(node.options, args[4]);
5196 
5197  if (num_args > 5) /* Has load weight override? */
5198  {
5199  if (node.options & Node::OPTION_l_LOAD_WEIGHT)
5200  {
5201  node.load_weight_override = STR_PARSE_REAL(args[5]);
5202  node._has_load_weight_override = true;
5203  }
5204  else
5205  {
5206  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, "Node has load-weight-override value specified, but option 'l' is not present. Ignoring value...");
5207  }
5208  }
5209  }
5210 
5211  m_current_module->nodes.push_back(node);
5212 }
5213 
5214 void Parser::_ParseSectionsNodesNodes2(Ogre::String const & line_in, bool is_version_2)
5215 {
5216  // Strip trailing comments
5217  std::string line;
5218  Parser::_TrimTrailingComments(line_in, line);
5219 
5220  // Parse line
5221  boost::smatch results;
5222  const boost::regex* regex_ptr = &Regexes::SECTION_NODES;
5223  if (is_version_2)
5224  {
5225  regex_ptr = &Regexes::SECTION_NODES_2;
5226  }
5227  if (! boost::regex_search(line, results, *regex_ptr))
5228  {
5229  if (m_sequential_importer.IsEnabled()) // Are we imporing legacy fileformat?
5230  {
5231  this->AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, "Failed to parse using safe method, falling back to classic method.");
5232  this->_ParseNodesLegacyMethod(line, is_version_2);
5233  }
5234  else
5235  {
5236  this->AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid line, ignoring...");
5237  }
5238  return;
5239  }
5240  /* NOTE: Positions in 'results' array match E_CAPTURE*() positions (starting with 1) in the respective regex. */
5241 
5242  const int result_pos_options = 11;
5243  const int result_pos_loadweightoverride = 15;
5244 
5245  Node node;
5246  node.node_defaults = m_user_node_defaults;
5247  node.beam_defaults = m_user_beam_defaults;
5248  node.detacher_group = m_current_detacher_group;
5249 
5250  if (is_version_2)
5251  {
5252  node.id.SetStr(results[1]);
5253  if (m_sequential_importer.IsEnabled())
5254  {
5255  m_sequential_importer.AddNamedNode(results[1]);
5256  }
5257  m_any_named_node_defined = true; // For import logic
5258  }
5259  else
5260  {
5261  const unsigned int node_num = static_cast<unsigned int>(STR_PARSE_INT(results[1]));
5262  node.id.SetNum(node_num);
5263  if (m_sequential_importer.IsEnabled())
5264  {
5265  m_sequential_importer.AddNumberedNode(node_num);
5266  }
5267  }
5268  node.position.x = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[3]);
5269  node.position.y = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[5]);
5270  node.position.z = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[7]);
5271 
5272  if (results[result_pos_options].matched) /* Has options? */
5273  {
5274  _ParseNodeOptions(node.options, results[result_pos_options]);
5275 
5276  if (results[result_pos_loadweightoverride].matched) /* Has load weight override? */
5277  {
5278  if (node.options & Node::OPTION_l_LOAD_WEIGHT)
5279  {
5280  node.load_weight_override = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[result_pos_loadweightoverride]);
5281  node._has_load_weight_override = true;
5282  }
5283  else
5284  {
5285  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, "Node has load-weight-override value specified, but option 'l' is not present. Ignoring value...");
5286  }
5287  }
5288  }
5289 
5290  m_current_module->nodes.push_back(node);
5291 }

5401 void Parser::VerifyAndProcessFlexBodyWheel(Ogre::String const & line, FlexBodyWheel& flexbody_wheel, int braking, int propulsion, char side_char)
5402 {
5403  // Axle rigidity node (9999 = null)
5404  if (flexbody_wheel.rigidity_node.IsValidAnyState() && flexbody_wheel.rigidity_node.Num() == 9999)
5405  {
5406  flexbody_wheel.rigidity_node.Invalidate();
5407  }
5408 
5409  if (braking < 0 || braking > 4)
5410  {
5411  this->AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid value of parameter ~7 (braking), using 0 (no braking)");
5412  braking = 0;
5413  }
5414  flexbody_wheel.braking = Wheels::Braking(braking);
5415 
5416  if (propulsion < 0 || propulsion > 2)
5417  {
5418  this->AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid value of parameter ~8 (propulsion), using 0 (no propulsion)");
5419  braking = 0;
5420  }
5421  flexbody_wheel.propulsion = Wheels::Propulsion(propulsion);
5422 
5423  flexbody_wheel.side = MeshWheel::SIDE_RIGHT;
5424  if (side_char != 'r')
5425  {
5426  if (side_char != 'l')
5427  {
5428  this->AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, std::string("Invalid SIDE flag (acceptable are [r/l]), parsing as LEFT for backwards compatibility: ") + side_char);
5429  }
5430  flexbody_wheel.side = MeshWheel::SIDE_LEFT;
5431  }
5432 
5433  if (m_sequential_importer.IsEnabled())
5434  {
5435  m_sequential_importer.GenerateNodesForWheel(File::KEYWORD_FLEXBODYWHEELS, flexbody_wheel.num_rays, flexbody_wheel.rigidity_node.IsValidAnyState());
5436  }
5437 
5438  m_current_module->flex_body_wheels.push_back(flexbody_wheel);
5439 }

5463 void Parser::ParseManagedMaterials(Ogre::String const & line)
5464 {
5465  boost::smatch results;
5466  if (! boost::regex_search(line, results, Regexes::SECTION_MANAGEDMATERIALS))
5467  {
5468  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid line, ignoring...");
5469  return;
5470  }
5471  /* NOTE: Positions in 'results' array match E_CAPTURE*() positions (starting with 1) in the respective regex. */
5472 
5473  ManagedMaterial managed_material;
5474  managed_material.options = m_current_managed_material_options;
5475  managed_material.name = results[1].str();
5476 
5477  managed_material.type = (results[4].matched) ? ManagedMaterial::TYPE_MESH_STANDARD : managed_material.type;
5478  managed_material.type = (results[5].matched) ? ManagedMaterial::TYPE_MESH_TRANSPARENT : managed_material.type;
5479  managed_material.type = (results[6].matched) ? ManagedMaterial::TYPE_FLEXMESH_STANDARD : managed_material.type;
5480  managed_material.type = (results[7].matched) ? ManagedMaterial::TYPE_FLEXMESH_TRANSPARENT : managed_material.type;
5481 
5482  managed_material.diffuse_map = results[9];
5483 
5484  if ( managed_material.type == ManagedMaterial::TYPE_MESH_STANDARD
5485  || managed_material.type == ManagedMaterial::TYPE_MESH_TRANSPARENT)
5486  {
5487  if (results[12].matched)
5488  {
5489  Ogre::String input = results[12];
5490  Ogre::StringUtil::trim(input);
5491 
5492  /*
5493  According to documentation, '-' is a placeholder for no texture.
5494  However, for compatibility with old parser, we need to only check the first letter and ignore the rest.
5495  */
5496  if (input.at(0) != '-')
5497  {
5498  managed_material.specular_map = input;
5499  }
5500  }
5501  }
5502  else
5503  {
5504  if (results[12].matched)
5505  {
5506  Ogre::String input = results[12];
5507 
5508  /*
5509  According to documentation, '-' is a placeholder for no texture.
5510  However, for compatibility with old parser, we need to only check the first letter and ignore the rest.
5511  */
5512  if (input.at(0) != '-')
5513  {
5514  managed_material.damaged_diffuse_map = input;
5515  }
5516  }
5517  if (results[15].matched)
5518  {
5519  Ogre::String input = results[15];
5520 
5521  /*
5522  According to documentation, '-' is a placeholder for no texture.
5523  However, for compatibility with old parser, we need to only check the first letter and ignore the rest.
5524  */
5525  if (input.at(0) != '-')
5526  {
5527  managed_material.specular_map = input;
5528  }
5529  }
5530  }
5531 
5532  m_current_module->managed_materials.push_back(managed_material);
5533 }

5592 bool Parser::_ParseOptionalInertia(OptionalInertia & inertia, boost::smatch & results, unsigned int start_index)
5593 {

5595 
5596  if (results[result_index].matched)
5597  {
5598  Ogre::String start_delay_str = results[result_index];
5599  inertia.start_delay_factor = STR_PARSE_REAL(start_delay_str);
5600  inertia._start_delay_factor_set = true;
5601 
5602  result_index += 3;
5603  if (results[result_index].matched)
5604  {
5605  Ogre::String stop_delay_str = results[result_index];
5606  inertia.stop_delay_factor = STR_PARSE_REAL(stop_delay_str);
5607  inertia._stop_delay_factor_set = true;
5608 
5609  result_index +=3;
5610  if (results[result_index].matched)
5611  {
5612  inertia.start_function = results[result_index];
5613 
5614  result_index += 3;
5615  if (results[result_index].matched)
5616  {
5617  inertia.stop_function = results[result_index];
5618  return true;
5619  }
5620  }
5621  }
5622  }
5623  return false;
5624 }

5626 void Parser::ParseBeams(Ogre::String const & _line)
5627 {
5628  const int FLAGS_INDEX = 7;
5629  const int EXT_LIMIT_INDEX = 11;
5630 
5631  std::string line;
5632  Parser::_TrimTrailingComments(_line, line);
5633 
5634  // Parse arguments
5635  boost::smatch results;
5636  if (! boost::regex_search(line, results, Regexes::SECTION_BEAMS))
5637  {
5638  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid line, ignoring...");
5639  return;
5640  }
5641  /* NOTE: Positions in 'results' array match E_CAPTURE*() positions (starting with 1) in the respective regex. */
5642 
5643  Beam beam;
5644  beam.defaults = m_user_beam_defaults;
5645  beam.detacher_group = m_current_detacher_group;
5646  beam.nodes[0] = _ParseNodeRef(results[1]);
5647  beam.nodes[1] = _ParseNodeRef(results[3]);
5648 
5649  /* Flags */
5650  if (results[FLAGS_INDEX].matched)
5651  {
5652  std::string const & flags_str = results[FLAGS_INDEX];
5653  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < flags_str.length(); i++)
5654  {
5655  if (flags_str[i] == 'v')
5656  {
5657  continue; // Dummy flag
5658  }
5659  if (flags_str[i] == 'i')
5660  {
5661  beam.options |= Beam::OPTION_i_INVISIBLE;
5662  }
5663  else if (flags_str[i] == 'r')
5664  {
5665  beam.options |= Beam::OPTION_r_ROPE;
5666  }
5667  else if (flags_str[i] == 's')
5668  {
5669  beam.options |= Beam::OPTION_s_SUPPORT;
5670  if (results[EXT_LIMIT_INDEX].matched)
5671  {
5672  beam._has_extension_break_limit = true;
5673  beam.extension_break_limit = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[EXT_LIMIT_INDEX]);
5674  }
5675  }
5676  else
5677  {
5678  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, std::string("Invalid flag: ") + flags_str[i]);
5679  }
5680  }
5681  }
5682 
5683  m_current_module->beams.push_back(beam);
5684 }

5686 void Parser::ParseAnimator(Ogre::String const & line)
5687 {
5688  boost::smatch results;
5689  if (! boost::regex_search(line, results, Regexes::SECTION_ANIMATORS))
5690  {
5691  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid line, ignoring...");
5692  return;
5693  }
5694  /* NOTE: Positions in 'results' array match E_CAPTURE*() positions (starting with 1) in the respective regex. */
5695 
5696  Animator animator;
5697  animator.inertia_defaults = m_user_default_inertia;
5698  animator.beam_defaults = m_user_beam_defaults;
5699  animator.detacher_group = m_current_detacher_group;
5700  animator.nodes[0] = _ParseNodeRef(results[1]);
5701  animator.nodes[1] = _ParseNodeRef(results[2]);
5702  animator.lenghtening_factor = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[3]);
5703 
5704  /* Parse options */
5705  /* Just use the split/trim/compare method */
5706  Ogre::StringVector tokens = Ogre::StringUtil::split(results[4].str(), "|");
5707  Ogre::StringVector::iterator iter = tokens.begin();
5708  while (iter != tokens.end())
5709  {
5710  Ogre::String token = *iter;
5711  Ogre::StringUtil::trim(token);
5712 
5713  /* Numbered keywords */
5714  if (boost::regex_search(token, results, Regexes::PARSE_ANIMATORS_NUMBERED_KEYWORD))
5715  {
5716  AeroAnimator aero_animator;
5717 
5718  if (results[1] == "throttle") animator.aero_animator.flags |= AeroAnimator::OPTION_THROTTLE;
5719  else if (results[1] == "rpm") animator.aero_animator.flags |= AeroAnimator::OPTION_RPM;
5720  else if (results[1] == "aerotorq") animator.aero_animator.flags |= AeroAnimator::OPTION_TORQUE;
5721  else if (results[1] == "aeropit") animator.aero_animator.flags |= AeroAnimator::OPTION_PITCH;
5722  else if (results[1] == "aerostatus") animator.aero_animator.flags |= AeroAnimator::OPTION_STATUS;
5723 
5724  animator.aero_animator.motor = STR_PARSE_INT(results[2]);
5725  }
5726  else if (boost::regex_search(token, results, Regexes::PARSE_ANIMATORS_KEY_COLON_VALUE))
5727  {
5728  if (results[1] == "shortlimit")
5729  {
5730  animator.short_limit = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[2]);
5731  animator.flags |= Animator::OPTION_SHORT_LIMIT;
5732  }
5733  else if(results[1] == "longlimit")
5734  {
5735  animator.long_limit = STR_PARSE_REAL(results[2]);
5736  animator.flags |= Animator::OPTION_LONG_LIMIT;
5737  }
5738  }
5739  else
5740  {
5741  /* Standalone keywords */
5742  if (token == "vis") animator.flags |= Animator::OPTION_VISIBLE;
5743  else if (token == "inv") animator.flags |= Animator::OPTION_INVISIBLE;
5744  else if (token == "airspeed") animator.flags |= Animator::OPTION_AIRSPEED;
5745  else if (token == "vvi") animator.flags |= Animator::OPTION_VERTICAL_VELOCITY;
5746  else if (token == "altimeter100k") animator.flags |= Animator::OPTION_ALTIMETER_100K;
5747  else if (token == "altimeter10k") animator.flags |= Animator::OPTION_ALTIMETER_10K;
5748  else if (token == "altimeter1k") animator.flags |= Animator::OPTION_ALTIMETER_1K;
5749  else if (token == "aoa") animator.flags |= Animator::OPTION_ANGLE_OF_ATTACK;
5750  else if (token == "flap") animator.flags |= Animator::OPTION_FLAP;
5751  else if (token == "airbrake") animator.flags |= Animator::OPTION_AIR_BRAKE;
5752  else if (token == "roll") animator.flags |= Animator::OPTION_ROLL;
5753  else if (token == "pitch") animator.flags |= Animator::OPTION_PITCH;
5754  else if (token == "brakes") animator.flags |= Animator::OPTION_BRAKES;
5755  else if (token == "accel") animator.flags |= Animator::OPTION_ACCEL;
5756  else if (token == "clutch") animator.flags |= Animator::OPTION_CLUTCH;
5757  else if (token == "speedo") animator.flags |= Animator::OPTION_SPEEDO;
5758  else if (token == "tacho") animator.flags |= Animator::OPTION_TACHO;
5759  else if (token == "turbo") animator.flags |= Animator::OPTION_TURBO;
5760  else if (token == "parking") animator.flags |= Animator::OPTION_PARKING;
5761  else if (token == "shifterman1") animator.flags |= Animator::OPTION_SHIFT_LEFT_RIGHT;
5762  else if (token == "shifterman2") animator.flags |= Animator::OPTION_SHIFT_BACK_FORTH;
5763  else if (token == "sequential") animator.flags |= Animator::OPTION_SEQUENTIAL_SHIFT;
5764  else if (token == "shifterlin") animator.flags |= Animator::OPTION_GEAR_SELECT;
5765  else if (token == "torque") animator.flags |= Animator::OPTION_TORQUE;
5766  else if (token == "difflock") animator.flags |= Animator::OPTION_DIFFLOCK;
5767  else if (token == "rudderboat") animator.flags |= Animator::OPTION_BOAT_RUDDER;
5768  else if (token == "throttleboat") animator.flags |= Animator::OPTION_BOAT_THROTTLE;
5769  }
5770 
5771  iter++;
5772  }
5773 
5774  m_current_module->animators.push_back(animator);

5777 void Parser::ParseAuthor(Ogre::String const & line)
5778 {
5779  if (! _IsCurrentModuleRoot())
5780  {
5781  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, "Inline-section 'author' has global effect and should not appear in a module");
5782  }
5783 
5784  boost::smatch results;
5785  if (! boost::regex_search(line, results, Regexes::INLINE_SECTION_AUTHOR))
5786  {
5787  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid line, ignoring...");
5788  return;
5789  }
5790 
5791  Author author;
5792 
5793  if (results[1].matched)
5794  {
5795  author.type = results[2].str();
5796  }
5797  else
5798  {
5799  AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING, "Inline-section 'author' has no parameters specified, ignoring...");
5800  return;
5801  }
5802 
5803  /* Forum account id */
5804  if (results[3].matched)
5805  {
5806  int user_id = STR_PARSE_INT(results[4]);
5807  if (user_id != -1)
5808  {
5809  author._has_forum_account = true;
5810  author.forum_account_id = user_id;
5811  }
5812 
5813  /* Name */
5814  if (results[5].matched)
5815  {
5816  author.name = results[6].str();
5817 
5818  /* Email */
5819  if (results[7].matched)
5820  {
5821  author.email = results[8].str();
5822  }
5823  }
5824  }
5825 
5826  m_definition->authors.push_back(author);
5827 }

5870 void Parser::AddMessage(std::string const & line, Message::Type type, std::string const & message)
5871 {
5872  /* Push and then access to avoid copy-constructing strings */
5873  m_messages.push_back(Message());
5874 
5875  m_messages.back().line = line;
5876  m_messages.back().line_number = m_current_line_number;
5877  m_messages.back().message = message;
5878  m_messages.back().type = type;
5879  m_messages.back().section = m_current_section;
5880  m_messages.back().subsection = m_current_subsection;
5881  m_messages.back().module = m_current_module->name;
5882 
5883  switch (type)
5884  {
5885  case Message::TYPE_ERROR:
5886  case Message::TYPE_FATAL_ERROR:
5887  ++m_messages_num_errors;
5888  break;
5889  case Message::TYPE_WARNING:
5890  ++m_messages_num_warnings;
5891  break;
5892  default:
5893  ++m_messages_num_other;
5894  break;
5895  }
5896 }
5897 
5898 File::Keyword Parser::IdentifyKeyword(Ogre::String const & line)
5899 {
5900  // Search with correct lettercase
5901  boost::smatch results;
5902  boost::regex_search(line, results, Regexes::IDENTIFY_KEYWORD_RESPECT_CASE); // Always returns true.
5903  File::Keyword keyword = FindKeywordMatch(results);
5904  if (keyword != File::KEYWORD_INVALID)
5905  {
5906  return keyword;
5907  }
5908 
5909  // Search and ignore lettercase
5910  boost::regex_search(line, results, Regexes::IDENTIFY_KEYWORD_IGNORE_CASE); // Always returns true.
5911  keyword = FindKeywordMatch(results);
5912  if (keyword != File::KEYWORD_INVALID)
5913  {
5914  this->AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING,
5915  "Keyword has invalid lettercase. Correct form is: " + std::string(File::KeywordToString(keyword)));
5916  }
5917  return keyword;
5918 }
5919 
5920 File::Keyword Parser::FindKeywordMatch(boost::smatch& search_results)
5921 {
5922  /* The 'results' array contains a complete match at positon [0] and sub-matches starting with [1],
5923  so we get exact positions in Regexes::IDENTIFY_KEYWORD, which again match File::Keyword enum members
5924  */
5925  for (unsigned int i = 1; i < search_results.size(); i++)
5926  {
5927  boost::ssub_match sub = search_results[i];
5928  if (sub.matched)
5929  {
5930  /* Build enum value directly from result offset */
5931  return File::Keyword(i);
5932  }
5933  }
5934  return File::KEYWORD_INVALID;
5935 }

5980 std::string Parser::ProcessMessagesToString()
5981 {
5982  if (this->GetMessages().size() == 0)
5983  {
5984  std::string msg(" == Parsing done OK, nothing to report");
5985  return msg;
5986  }
5987 
5988  std::stringstream report;
5989  report << " == Parsing done, report:" << std::endl <<std::endl;
5990 
5991  auto itor = m_messages.begin();
5992  auto end = m_messages.end();
5993  for (; itor != end; ++itor)
5994  {
5995  switch (itor->type)
5996  {
5997  case (RigDef::Parser::Message::TYPE_FATAL_ERROR):
5998  report << "#FF3300 FATAL_ERROR #FFFFFF";
5999  break;
6000 
6001  case (RigDef::Parser::Message::TYPE_ERROR):
6002  report << "#FF3300 ERROR #FFFFFF";
6003  break;
6004 
6005  case (RigDef::Parser::Message::TYPE_WARNING):
6006  report << "#FFFF00 WARNING #FFFFFF";
6007  break;
6008 
6009  default:
6010  report << "INFO";
6011  break;
6012  }
6013  report << " (Section " << RigDef::File::SectionToString(itor->section) << ")" << std::endl;
6014  report << "\tLine (" << itor->line_number << "): " << itor->line << std::endl;
6015  report << "\tMessage: " << itor->message << std::endl;
6016  }
6017 
6018  return report.str();
6019 }
6020 
6021 int Parser::_ParseArgs(std::string const & line, Ogre::StringVector &args, unsigned min_num_args)
6022 {
6023  // Note: This splitting silently ignores multiple consecutive separators.
6024  // For example "A,|,B" will produce results[0] = "A", results[1] = "B"
6025  try
6026  {
6027  args = Ogre::StringUtil::split(line, ":|, \t");
6028  if (args.size() < min_num_args)
6029  {
6030  std::stringstream msg;
6031  msg << "Too few arguments, minimum is: " << min_num_args;
6032  this->AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, msg.str());
6033  args.clear();
6034  return -1;
6035  }
6036  return args.size();
6037  }
6038  catch(Ogre::Exception &e)
6039  {
6040  this->AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Unexpected error while parsing line: "+e.getFullDescription());
6041  args.clear();
6042  return -1;
6043  }
6044 }
